title: peanut brittle
directions: Place first 3 ingredients into pan.
Cook at medium heat. When mixture boils, cover with lid for 3 minutes.
Remove lid. Stir in margarine, cook to 260°.
Stir in peanuts, continue stirring and cook to 310°.
Remove from heat, add baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Pour batch on greased baking sheet.
Let cool slightly.
Loosen from sheet, turn over and stretch as thin as possible.

title: mary ann's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in covered skillet with Pam until white. Cut into small pieces or strips.
Mix together in bowl the cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Add chicken and pour into casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers and spread over chicken mixture.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Serve hot chicken mixture over rice.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch thoroughly in top of double boiler. Blend in boiling water.
Cook over direct heat (stirring constantly) until mixture thickens and boils.
Then set over boiling water and cook 10 minutes more stirring constantly.
Beat egg yolks slightly, then blend into them some of the hot thickened mixture.
Then blend the egg yolk mixture into cornstarch mixture in double boiler.
Blend in butter, lemon juice and lemon rind, then remove from over boiling water and cool.
Place in baked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown very slightly in oven.

title: pudding pie
directions: Mix by hand.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: cherry pineapple salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: squares
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Pour into an ungreased cookie sheet or large cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate bits and walnuts over the top. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Let cool and stir in pie filling, pineapple and nuts.
Let set up and then add topping.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Mix flour with sour cream.
Combine with all other ingredients except chicken and mushrooms.
Place chicken in baking dish with mushrooms filling in.
Pour mixture over all.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Put into loaf pan.
Spoon catsup on.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spicy texas chili
directions: Trim meat and cut into small chunks.
Place meat in a microsafe dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Add 1/2 cup water. Microwave at High power for about 12 minutes, turning meat over and around after 6 minutes.
Add vinegar, bouillon cubes, chili powder, onions and green pepper.
Add another 1/4 cup water. Microwave at High power for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring once during cooking.

title: stromboli
directions: Take 1 loaf frozen unbaked bread and let rise according to directions on package.
Roll bread into rectangular shape.
Layer dough with Mozzarella cheese, thin sliced ham, salami, tomatoes and pepperoni.
Top with another layer of cheese.
Sprinkle to taste with spices.

title: bagels
directions: Mix in small bowl water, sugar and salt.
Add in 3/4 cup flour and yeast.
Mix 1/2 minute on low, then 3 minutes on high.
Stir in the rest of the flour until it's kneadable.
Knead for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover for 15 minutes.
Make 6 bagels.
Cover 20 minutes. Boil 1 gallon of water plus 1 tablespoon sugar.
Turn to medium. Cook bagels 7 minutes in water, half on each side.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: oatmeal applesauce bread(diabetic)
directions: Mix oats, flour, all-bran, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in applesauce, oil and eggs until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts until well mixed.
Put into a lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out on rack to cool completely.
Yields one loaf (18 slices, 1/2-inch thick).

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add apples and nutmeats, mixing thoroughly.
Bake in a greased pan at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip, if desired.

title: tomato juice cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add the tomato juice, then the dry ingredients.
Add the nuts or raisins.
Bake in greased pans for about 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost with a white icing.

title: chicken breasts with lemon-pepper sauce(microwave)
directions: Remove skin from chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with Creole seasoning.
Place breasts in a 1-quart casserole dish; cover with lid.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients except for the stuffing.
Pour mixture over broccoli. Top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jane's pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and bake in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish for 40 minutes at 350°.
Frost when cooled.

title: fruit dip with fruit
directions: Cream the cheese and marshmallow cream together, adding the orange juice.
Cut melons into chunks.
Slice the bananas into bite sized portions.
Place the bowl of dip in the middle of a medium tray and surround with fruit.
Servings-32.

title: split pickles
directions: Put pickles in water.
Leave the pickles in the brine for one week.
Drain brine off and cover with clear boiling water.
Leave pickles in this water for 24 hours.
Drain off and cover with boiling water into which place a lump of alum the size of hulled walnut.
Leave pickles in this water for 24 hours, take out, drain and pack in jars.
Cover with the next 6 ingredients, boiling hot. Leave pickles in this 24 hours, drain, heat mixture boiling hot and cover pickles.
Repeat this in 24 hours, then seal pickles.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix fruit and 3/4 cup sugar.
(Omit sugar if using prepared fruit like fruit cocktail.)
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: **apple cake
directions: A few raisins may be added.
Bake in long or tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil together.
May add anything else that you care to add or have in the house, such as: icing, M&M's, chocolate chips, nuts, miniature peanut butter cups or a kissy in the center.
Bake at 350° until edges barely begin to brown.
Can be made on cookie sheet or in a miniature cupcake/muffin pan.

title: pepperoni pizza casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in skillet. Cook over medium heat, stirring until meat crumbles and browns; drain well. Stir in pizza sauce, garlic salt, macaroni and 1 cup cheese. Spoon mixture into lightly greased 11 x 17 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Arrange pepperoni on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 5 additional minutes.

title: vanilla wafer coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in next 2 ingredients.
Beat in one egg at a time, stirring in pecans and coconut.
Turn into a greased and floured pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inch. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt Milky Way bars (chipped one to two at a time).
Add a little milk to the melted bars as they melt.
Stir until all bars are mixed well.
Remove from heat and add to remaining ingredients. Pour into ice cream freezer.
Add milk to the "fill line" on your freezer.
Churn and freeze according to your individual freezer's directions.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Combine with sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Chill dough for at least an hour.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough in powdered sugar.
Roll to coat.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
These cookies are sold at Toots Sweets.
Yumm!!

title: pizza dip
directions: In a small bowl beat together cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder and red pepper.
Spread evenly in a 9-inch pie pan.
Spread pizza sauce over top.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese, bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Makes 1 1/4 cup or 12 servings.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash, onions and salt.
Let sit for 1 or 2 hours. Drain.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to stand and soften for 1 hour.
Grate cucumber and drain excess liquid.
Add Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Combine all ingredients together, let stand for another 20 to 30 minutes before serving with pretzels, crackers or chips.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls. Place meat balls in an ungreased baking dish.
Stir together tomato sauce, 1 cup water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meat balls.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover the last 15 minutes.

title: st. croix citrus brownies(makes 32 brownies)
directions: Blend; press into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake 20 minutes until golden at 350°.
Remove and reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: In a shallow dish, combine the egg, milk, and salt.
Mix well.
Put the flour in another shallow dish. Place the dill pickle slices on paper towels to dry slightly.
Dip slices in egg mixture, then coat with flour.
Heat oil (about 1/4 inch deep) in electric skillet to 375 degrees.
Fry pickle slices, turning to lightly brown each side. Drain well on paper towels.

title: banana shake
directions: Measure dry milk powder and ice water into container of electric blender.
Cover and process at low speed until well mixed.
Peel banana and cut into chunks, add to blender with vanilla, cover and process until smooth.
Add ice cubes and process at high speed until melted.
Makes 1 serving; 170 calories.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and cool.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard; beat again.
Add bread crumbs and stir.
Add cheese, sausage and mushrooms and stir.
Put in greased glass baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in 1-quart dish or 30 minutes in a 2-quart dish.

title: pumpkin and cream cheese roll-up
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with wax paper; grease and flour the wax paper.
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice, nutmeg and salt onto wax paper.
Beat eggs and sugar in large bowl until thick and fluffy; beat in pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients all at once. Pour into prepared pan; spread evenly with rubber spatula. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 15 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched with fingertip.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Combine hot milk, sugar, salt and Crisco.
Stir until shortening is melted and cool.
Mix yeast and lukewarm water.
Stir and let set a few minutes.
Combine with first mixture and add beaten egg.
Stir in flour and let set until twice the size.

title: coffee cake(makes 8 servings)
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 1 1/4 cups flour with granulated sugar, baking powder and salt.
With pastry blender or two knives used scissor-fashion, cut in 3 tablespoons margarine until mixture resembles coarse meal.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs together until sugar has dissolved. Add flour and vanilla extract.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly-greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: meatballs
directions: Stir all the ingredients together and put in loaf pans.
Top with the topping mixture.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Place rice in dish.
Salt and pepper chicken and arrange on top of rice.
Add cream of mushroom soup and water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange salad
directions: Bring to a boil
and
thicken
until
glazy
and clear, stirring constantly.
Put in bowl and chill thoroughly.
Add 2 cups Cool Whip and mandarin oranges.
Keep cool.

title: italian-style turkey cutlets
directions: Mix turkey thoroughly with Ricotta, parsley, salt and pepper. Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan on a shallow plate.
Shape turkey into 4 flat cutlets.
Press the cutlets into the crumb mixture, coating both sides lightly.
Spray a shallow, no-stick skillet with cooking spray.
Fry the cutlets, with no fat added, about 3 or 4 minutes on each side.
Makes 4 servings with 295 calories each.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, milk, bread and salt.
Pour in pudding dish.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until a knife blade inserted near the center comes out clean.
Serve with cream or lemon sauce.

title: jello cola salad or bing cola salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Combine juices to make 1 1/4 cups liquid.
Heat juices; pour over gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add cherries, pineapple and cola.
Chill.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Put all ingredients into mixing bowl at once time in electric mixer.
Beat on high for 5 minutes or longer.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and flavorings together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Chill. Scoop cookies onto baking sheet.
Flatten each cookie with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
You may also add chocolate chips, pecans, 1 cup coconut and raisins.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In medium bowl, mix mayonnaise with lemon juice.
With small sharp knife, dice apples (do not peel).
Add diced apples to mayonnaise and lemon juice mixture.
Stir to coat well.
Add sliced celery, walnuts and raisins.
Toss gently to mix well. Arrange lettuce leaves on serving platter.
Spoon salad into center.

title: fruit salad
directions: I also add about 1 can chunk pineapple, drained.

title: monkey bread
directions: You will need 2 (9-inch) ring molds.

title: homestyle potato chips
directions: Slice potatoes thinly, as many as desired.
Heat grease to 400°.
Drop potato slice into hot grease and cook until they float to top.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: wild goose with raspberries
directions: Season goose with salt and white pepper.
Mix raspberry preserves and brandy for roasting.
Place goose on a bed of sliced carrots, celery and onions in a roasting pan.
Roast in a 325° oven, basting every 10 minutes with raspberry preserves and brandy mixture.
To check for doneness, pierce goose between breast and thigh.
If liquid runs clear, goose is done.
Serve with salad and baked potatoes with chive topping.
Serves 4. Preparation Time:
2 1/2 hours.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package and drain. Add celery, onion, grated cheese, water chestnuts and salad dressing.
Thoroughly mix and spread into long baking dish.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter with cream over moderate heat and stir until butter is melted and cream comes to a low boil.
Add sugars and stir until dissolved.
Reduce heat and add cocoa.
Remove from heat when mixture is smooth.
This must be stored in refrigerator. May be served warm or hot.

title: open house punch
directions: Mix all ingredients. Serve over ice or place in punch bowl. You can spike this with bourbon.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and rinse with cold water.
Add vegetables. Pour dressing over this, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Chill.

title: cherry pie supreme
directions: With electric mixer, blend together cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla
until creamy and smooth.
Fill pie shell with 3/4 can cherry
filling.
Pour
cheese
mixture into shell and top with remaining
filling in middle of pie.
Chill for 2 or more hours.

title: chocolate chip, date, nut cake
directions: Pour water over dates and add 1 teaspoon soda.
Let cool. Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add date mixture.
Then sift flour, salt and 3/4 teaspoon soda.
Mix into other ingredients.
Put into 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased and floured.
Put mixture of sugar and chocolate chips.
Place nuts on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: picante sauce
directions: Cook 45 minutes.
Cool 1/2 cup juice and add 3 tablespoons cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Put into hot jars.
Seal and turn upside-down until cool.

title: low-fat chicken pie
directions: Tear chicken into bite size pieces and cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole pan.
Layer corn, peas and eggs.
Heat soup in water from chicken and pour over casserole.
Mix Butter Buds, hot water, flour and buttermilk and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and 425° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: blackberry jam pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar to which the flour has been added.
Pour in milk, melted butter; jam and the vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 425°.
Let cool, then top with Cool Whip or meringue.

title: fluffy tapioca pudding(from 1975 edition)
directions: Mix tapioca, salt, 3 tablespoons sugar, milk and yolk in pan. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Beat egg white until foamy; gradually beat in 2 tablespoons sugar, beating to soft peaks.
Set aside.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in bowl.
Then add flour, 2 cups at a time.
Place in a bowl (greased) and cover with a damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator.
You can keep it in refrigerator for about 3 days.
Make into buns or loaves and let rise about 2 hours before baking.
Bake in 400° oven until done.

title: no-bake chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding and milk; mix well. Fold in whipped topping. Layer 1 package of graham crackers in bottom of 8 x 11-inch pan. Spread half of pudding mixture evenly over the graham crackers. Repeat with the second package of graham crackers and the rest of the pudding mixture. Place third package of graham crackers on top. Immediately spread the chocolate frosting over all. Place a piece of plastic wrap over cake and refrigerate overnight. (This is a must so that the graham crackers will get soft.) Enjoy.

title: caribbean chicken and rice
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add water to measure 1 3/4 cups.
Salt and pepper chicken.
In large skillet, brown sausage and set aside.
Add chicken and brown, drain.
Add sausage, rice, garlic, allspice and reserved liquid.
Bring to boil; cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes or until chicken is done.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cook 5 minutes.

title: grape-nut bread
directions: Mix Grape-Nuts, buttermilk and eggs and set aside.
Sift together the rest of dry ingredients.
Then mix with all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for one hour in 2 greased and floured pans.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: kosher green tomato dill pickles
directions: Choose small firm green tomatoes.
Wash thoroughly and pack into clean jars.
To each quart, add a garlic clove, a stalk of celery and a 1/4 of a green pepper.
Make solution of water, vinegar and salt.
Add 1 head dill for each jar and boil solution 5 minutes.
Pour solution over green tomatoes in jars, placing dill in each.
Seal and store 6 weeks.
Pickles will not be thoroughly cured before that time.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add rice.
Add cooked shrimp and cheese.
Combine milk, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix and pour.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: lemon graham slice
directions: Combine the ingredients together well.
Pack into a 9 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Set aside.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain off grease.
Place meat in bottom of casserole dish, top with Tater Tots, then pour over soup.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "bea-beas" cornbread
directions: Mix all
together.
Bake
in greased pan at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Can be frozen to use later.

title: cocoa
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Pour into 1/3 cup of hot water in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil and stir constantly.
Boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Add milk.
Stir and heat (do not boil).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Serve hot with marshmallows, if desired.
Refrigerate until cold.
Shake well before serving. Tastes like "Dutch" chocolate milk.
Use 1/2 teaspoon mint extract instead of vanilla for mint cocoa.

title: june's chili
directions: Pat meat dry.
Heat tablespoon oil in large pot.
Add meat at once.
Sear it turning until all browned.
Put meat in a bowl.
Add 2 tablespoon onions and garlic, saute until limp, not brown.
Add chili and spices.
Add broth, tomato paste, sugar and salt and break tomatoes as stirring.
Add meat, cover and simmer 40-50 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna spread
directions: Soften cream cheese, crumble tuna and mix together.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Mound on plate and garnish with parsley; serve with crackers.

title: cry baby cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add molasses, then milk and soda.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans and sprinkle over bottom of 11 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix cake well and pour over coconut and pecans. Mix sugar, cream cheese and oleo together and pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Fill crumb crust with ice cream. Freeze. Spread whipped cream around edge before serving.

title: noodle kugel(low-fat)
directions: Cook noodles; rinse and drain according to package instructions.
Melt margarine, then combine it with sugar, eggs and vanilla in blender.
Add sour cream and cottage cheese to cooked noodles.
Add mixture from blender; stir well.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Serves 6 or more.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Stir in bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, cream, milk, sugar and seasonings.
Cook 5 minutes. Mix 2 tablespoons butter and the flour; add slowly to cooked mixture, stirring until thickened.
Serve.

title: prize cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Gradually add to shortening mixture.
Mix.
Stir in mincemeat.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Put popcorn in ungreased large pan.
Mix together butter, corn syrup and sugar.
Heat until bubbly.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soda.
(Mixture will become foamy.)
Pour over corn and stir.
Bake in 200° oven 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pear crisp
directions: Mix all dry parts until crumbly.
Put pears into 1/4 wedges in baking dish.
Toss lemon juice on top.
Sprinkle dry mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and pour over stuffing.
Line bottom of casserole with half of stuffing mixture.
Cook squash and onion in salted water for 5 minutes.*
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots.
Fold in squash.
Pour over stuffing in casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach 5 minutes in microwave; drain well.
Beat eggs. Add remaining ingredients.
Make one-inch balls.
Arrange on 2 plates and cook in microwave for 3 minutes each plate.
Be sure to cover while cooking.
These may be frozen and cooked, a few at a time, as needed.

title: cranberry christmas punch
directions: Boil berries, oranges and lemons (sliced with peel, for 20 minutes.)
Strain and add sugar and spices.
Serve hot or cold. Makes 2 quarts.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Stir all ingredients together (with melted oleo). Pour into shell. Bake 1 hour or until filling is set and browned.

title: jam tarts
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter.
Beat until well blended. Stir in flour and salt.
Mix well.
Form into a ball.
Cover. Chill for 30 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus squares
directions: Beat 1 egg and combine with cake mix and margarine.
Put into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and stir in powdered sugar.
Add coconut and pecans.
Spread over cake.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: dilled green beans(sisterhood banquet '94)
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan.
Blend in flour; drain liquid from beans and add gradually, making a thin sauce.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings and beans. Serves 4.

title: herb biscuits
directions: Melt butter
in
pie
tin.
Stir
in cheese, dill weed, onion flakes
and parsley flakes.
Cut biscuits into quarters. Fill pie tin
and bake per instructions on biscuit can at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: grits casserole
directions: Bake in a greased Pyrex dish at 325° for 1 hour.

title: acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half and scoop out seeds.
Turn squash upside down on oiled baking pan.
Bake in oven at 400° for 30 minutes (or longer if larger squash).
Turn upwards and place 1 tablespoon of butter and 1 tablespoon of
brown sugar in each half.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes more, or until done.
Serves 2.

title: carl's best brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large microwave-safe bowl place butter.
Microwave at High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with spoon after each addition.
Add cocoa; beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; beat well. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Makes 36 brownies.

title: toll house pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugars; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: ham and egg pie
directions: Make a thin white sauce of butter, flour, salt and milk. Combine ham, eggs and sauce in pan.
Make crust to cover or use ready-made crust.
Dot with butter and brown.

title: scripture cake
directions: For mixing, follow advice of Solomon (Proverbs 23:14).

title: summer sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into two logs. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake in 300° to 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine everything except cheese and chips.
Place in well-greased casserole. Sprinkle with cheese, then chips.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Serve hot.
Freezes well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix together the hash browns, cream of chicken soup, sour cream, onion, 1/2 cup of butter, salt and pepper, then put in baking dish and set aside.
In a bowl, mix 1 cup of butter and crackers.
Spread over top of potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: willie pearl's frozen cherry salad
directions: Drain fruits and reserve a few cherries and orange segments for garnish.
Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Beat until fluffy and blend in sour cream, sugar and salt.
Fold in fruits, marshmallows and pecans.
Pour into loaf pan and freeze 6 hours or overnight.
Unmold and garnish with orange segments and cherries.
Makes 8 servings.
May be frozen in muffin cups.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water to 260°.
Add pecans and salt and cook to 290°.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and soda.
Stir well and quickly.
Pour in two cookie sheets, buttered.
When cool, break as desired.

title: pizza macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown hamburg.
Add onion, salt and pepper. Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, spices and seasonings. Let cook 10 minutes.
Mix with macaroni.
Place half in casserole. Put in layer of cheese, pepperoni and mushrooms.
Put in layers of all ingredients until gone.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cover with lid or foil.

title: butter bean bake
directions: Partly cook bacon and drain on paper towel.
Brown onion and pepper in drippings.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Put all ingredients in a buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake 40 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: cheese strata
directions: Arrange six slices of bread in a 9 x 13-inch greased Pyrex dish.
Cover bread with cheese.
Arrange remaining bread on top of cheese.
Blend remaining ingredients; pour evenly over bread.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chutney-peanut spread
directions: Mix curry powder into softened cream cheese. Spread onto bottom of low-sided serving platter or dish. Cover with layer of minced chutney.
Next, put a layer of chopped green onion. Sprinkle coconut next, then finally the layer of honey roasted peanuts.
Let the guests spread their own on a sturdy cracker.

title: easy grasshopper pie
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine.
Press onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Refrigerate.
Melt marshmallows with creme de menthe stirring until smooth.
Refrigerate 20 minutes or until slightly thickened.

title: sopillos or sopaipillas
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Cool milk to just warm and add.
Roll out to thin pie crust thickness.
Cut in 2-inch squares and fry in deep hot fat.
Yields 30.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together; pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple.
Place in lightly greased casserole dish. Combine flour and sugar; sprinkle over pineapple.
Top with cheese and then the cracker crumbs.
Dot with oleo.
Bake at 325° about 25 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Melt 1 stick oleo and use 1/2 with recipe and 1/2 with crushed cornflakes for topping.
Can be frozen.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: party cheese terrine
directions: Oil 1 small loaf pan or Tupperware cheese container with lid. Stir together chopped nuts and 3 tablespoons parsley.
Spread evenly in bottom of pan.
In medium bowl, beat together cream cheese, margarine and milk until smooth.
For first layer, spread 1/3 of cheese mixture evenly over nuts.
Second layer, transfer half of remaining cheese mixture to another bowl.
Stir in remaining parsley and onions.
Spread over cheese layer already in loaf pan.
Third layer, stir deviled ham, diced pimento and mustard into remaining cheese.
Spread over other layers in pan. Chill overnight.
Invert on tray or Tupperware lid to serve.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Beat with wire whisk. There will be small lumps.
Cook in a Pam-covered skillet.
May use oil if you like.

title: century old gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and molasses. Sift dry ingredients together and mix.
Add hot water last and beat until smooth.
Bake in shallow pan for 45 minutes at 350°. Serve with thin sugar frosting.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Mix ground tomatoes and sugar in a large pan.
Heat and stir until boiling.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add gelatin.
Cool slightly.
Put in plastic container and freeze.
When using, store in refrigerator.
Will keep about two weeks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove skin and bones and cut in chunks.
Mix uncooked rice, celery and onion with chicken.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into shells.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: strawberry sipper
directions: Place ingredients in blender and whip until smooth and frothy. Serve immediately.

title: yummy orange balls
directions: Put vanilla wafers in a Ziploc bag and crush by rolling a glass over them.
Mix
crushed
wafers,
powdered
sugar and nuts. Add melted butter
and
thawed
orange juice; mix well. Roll into small balls and roll in coconut.
Store in refrigerator overnight. They also freeze well.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice according to package.
In a large skillet, add rice, vegetables, meat, seasoning and green onion.
Move the whole rice mixture over to the side.
Pour in eggs.
Cook the eggs.
As they begin to cook, stir them into the mixture.
Add soy sauce until the color of
the rice is a slight golden brown.
Fry the rice mixture; add salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut together; let set for 10 minutes.
Place 2 sections of cake in pan or glass dish.
Cover with mixture.
Place remaining cake on top of bottom layer.
Mix whipped topping with remaining mixture and frost whole cake. Refrigerate several hours.
Great next day!

title: angel food delight
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cream the cheese, sugar and milk.
Add Cool Whip and drained pineapple.
Split angel food cake into 3 layers. Spread creamed mixture between layers and frost with remaining mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: norwegian pecan cookies
directions: Work mixture well with hands.
Mix in order given.
Shape in crescents and bake in a slow oven (250° to 300°).
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix well and pat 1/2-inch thick on cookie sheet.
Chill or freeze overnight or several hours.
Break into pieces and roll in flour.
Brown quickly on both sides.
Put in casserole and cover with mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamed spinach pastry shells
directions: Cook spinach per package directions.
Drain.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Bake pastry shells for 12 minutes at 375°. Let shells cool.
Add spinach mix.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°. Serve warm.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix and cool first 4 ingredients.
Then mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 375° until bread starts to rise.
Turn down oven to 300°.
Bake about 1 hour.
Can be baked in 7 medium size cans, greased and floured.

title: sharon's favorite lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan, cook beef and garlic over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Stir in the water, tomato sauce and paste, soup mix, oregano, sugar and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat sauce into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer with three noodles and a third of the cottage cheese, Mozzarella, meat and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers twice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly and heated through. Uncover; bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: kugel
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for 8 minutes; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sally's dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake well before using.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and butter.
Mix as for a pie crust. Add beaten egg and milk.
Pat in bottom and sides of a 9-inch square greased pan.
Place rhubarb on crust.
Sprinkle dry gelatin over rhubarb.
Over this, sprinkle streusel topping, made by mixing 1 cup sugar, flour and butter together.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 9.

title: microwave pickles
directions: Mix together in a microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes (stirring twice) until pickles are crisp.
Put in jars and refrigerate.

title: dump cake
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Spray the bottom of a regular size cake pan with Pam (very lightly).
Pour both cans of cherries into pan and spread evenly.
Pour crushed pineapple over cherries.
(Do not drain juice from pineapple).
Pour cake mix over pineapple.
(Do not mix cake mix; pour it over pineapple dry.)
Melt the stick of butter and pour it over dry cake mix.
Pour nuts over melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and limeade, then add Cool Whip and a couple drops green food coloring.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate several hours before serving. Garnish with lime slices before serving.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus.
Arrange half of asparagus in a 2 quart casserole dish.
Cover with drained peas.
Mix mushroom soup, mayonnaise, grated Cheddar cheese, salt, pepper, onion and beaten eggs to make a sauce.
Pour half of the sauce over the asparagus and peas.
Add remaining asparagus.
Top with remaining sauce. Sprinkle crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven.
Add tomatoes, potatoes, carrots, onion, salt, pepper and water.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 45 minutes.
Add rice and simmer 20 or more minutes or until rice is done.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Simmer eggplant in pan of boiling salted water for 10 minutes. Drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole as follows:
1/2 of tomatoes, eggplant, bread crumbs, seasonings, tomato sauce and cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix margarine and cheese thoroughly.
Blend in flour.
Shape into roll, about the diameter of a quarter.
Chill overnight. Slice wafers 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: french toast - overnight
directions: Cover with plastic wrap; put in refrigerator. Bake next a.m. at 350°, uncovered.

title: crabmeat english muffins
directions: Melt the butter and add the jar of cheese spread.
Heat slowly until melted.
Add crab meat, mayonnaise and spices.
Spoon and spread onto split English muffins.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes until browned.

title: terrarine
directions: Brown and strain ground beef.
Put all ingredients, except cheese and noodles, in big pot.
Cook until thick.
Let simmer while cooking and cover.
After done, boil noodles in separate pan, then add to big pot.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer, then put in big casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan; set aside.
Mix all ingredients, except peaches in bowl.
Pour in pan that butter was melted in.
Pour peaches on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven or until brown.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Place chicken between two sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap. Pound to 1/4 inch thickness, using a mallet or rolling pin.
Place chicken in large shallow container; set side.
Combine molasses, ginger, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, oil and lemon juice; stir well.
Pour mixture over chicken breasts and marinate 8 hours in refrigerator.
Saute mushrooms and green onions in 1/8 cup butter, stirring constantly until liquid has evaporated.

title: bruschetta sauce
directions: Chop garlic very fine, chop basil, cilantro and parsley in food processor.
Add garlic and tomatoes; mix well.
Add olive oil and balsamic vinegar, salt and pepper.
Use as you would salsa as a dip or use with meat.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt. Stir in egg yolks 1 at a time. Alternate with buttermilk, flour and soda in water. Beat until smooth. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°. Cool 10 minutes. Run knife to loosen. Turn out. Wonderful for strawberry shortcake.

title: vegetable beef stew
directions: In heavy pan, stir beef in 1 tablespoon oil until no longer pink.
Add vegetables except for peas.
Add water to cover; bring to a boil and turn heat down.
Simmer 2 hours, then add Durkee beef stew seasoning mix which has been thoroughly dissolved in 1 cup warm water.
Stir into the vegetable mixture and cook 1 hour (simmer).
Add the peas; cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Put the 1/2 cup sugar in skillet and melt until an amber color, stirring constantly.
Add the 1/2 cup water and let it boil a short time until well mixed.
Set aside.

title: salsa bolognese
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; lightly brown bacon, then take off. Add onions, carrots and celery.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes. Add the beef and pork (ground together); cook, stirring almost steadily for 5 minutes.
Mix in the wine and chipped bacon.
Cook until evaporated.
Stir in tomato paste, 1 cup broth, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add mushrooms and remaining broth.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes. Taste for seasoning.
Mix in heavy cream.
Serve with pasta.

title: untraditional oatmeal cookies
directions: First, mash the bananas with a fork or blend in a blender to a liquid.
Place in a large bowl and mix the sugar, vanilla and egg substitute with the bananas.
Mix together the flour, oatmeal, baking powder and soda.
Alternately add the flour mixture and the milk to the banana mixture and finally add the nuts.
Preheat the oven to 375° and spray a cookie sheet with Pam or Baker's Joy (mixture of oil and flour).
Plop the batter 1 teaspoonful at a time onto the sheet and bake for 10 minutes, until the cookies are just barely browned at the edges.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and vegetable oil well. Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, carrots and walnuts and blend. Bake at 325° in 1 layer in 9 x 13 pan for 45 to 55 minutes or in 2 layers in 8 x 8 pans for 40 minutes or in 3 loaf pans for 55 minutes.

title: baked clams
directions: Cream the first four ingredients and then slowly beat in the beer.
Now put a small amount of the mixture on each clam.
Cut the bacon in sizes large enough to cover each clam (1/2 shell). Sprinkle bread crumbs over all and arrange on an oiled baking dish. bake in a 300° to 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: karo fudge
directions: Cook until forms soft ball in water. Beat until cool. Put in greased pan or spoon out on waxed paper.

title: taco casserole
directions: Simmer for 10 minutes.
Put chips in casserole dish; crumble coarsely.
Pour mixture on top.
Sprinkle sharp Cheddar cheese over top.
Put in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spanish rolls
directions: Grind together all ingredients and mix with tomato sauce and garlic.
Split rolls, fill with mix.
Wrap each in foil.
Place in covered roaster.
Bake 1 hour at 200°.

title: black beans
directions: Wash beans thoroughly and soak overnight in water.
Use this water for cooking.
Fry slightly the onion, green pepper and garlic in olive oil.
Combine all ingredients, except vinegar, which is added a few minutes before beans are ready to serve. Cook with low heat until beans are tender and the liquid is of thick consistency.

title: little cookie cup surprises
directions: You will need a mini muffin pan.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring to boil in large container, then add cucumber slices. Heat just to boiling point.
Do not boil.
Stir often with wooden spoon.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: walking taco
directions: Spread both cans jalapeno dip onto a large round platter.
Mix and spread onto beans the sour cream, taco mix and mayonnaise. Sprinkle the diced chilies over sour cream mixture.
Next, layer the 4 ripe avocados, mashed with lime juice and garlic powder.
End with grated Cheddar cheese, chopped tomatoes, onions and olives and surround with tortilla chips.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Layer lettuce, peas, celery, broccoli, onions, eggs and bacon. Combine salad dressing and sugar.
Put as next layer.
Put another layer of lettuce, bacon and green pepper.
Top with cheese.

title: raspberry chews
directions: Cream butter or
margarine
with
cup
sugar until fluffy and light in
a
medium bowl.
Beat in egg yolks.
Stir in flour until well
blended.
Spread evenly in an ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place batter into three 9-inch greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw bread.
Make little balls.
Make single layer in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place brown sugar, pudding, margarine and milk in top of double boiler.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over dough balls.
Cover with Saran Wrap and let rise until double in size. Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Mix graham cracker crumbs with half of the margarine. Put this in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan and chill.

title: mac and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add beef; cook until brown.
Add tomatoes and simmer while macaroni cooks per package label.
Layer macaroni in casserole dish.
Add layer of tomato mixture and cheeses.
Should be about three layers.
Pour 1/4 cup milk over entire casserole.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Should be heated all the way through.

title: lizzie's rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
The flavor is better if the rice is combined with the salad dressing while the rice is still hot.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix ingredients well. Spoon into greased muffin pan. Cook in preheated oven at 450° until lightly brown.

title: kid-size pizzas
directions: Use a knife to divide each English muffin.
Place English muffins (inside up) on a baking sheet.
Brown hamburger meat in skillet and drain.
Mix hamburger meat with Pizza Quick sauce. Spoon hamburger mixture onto each English muffin.
Let kids help top the meat mixture with the cheese and pepperoni.
Bake the pizzas at 350° for approximately 10 minutes until cheese melts and is bubbly.
Enjoy!

title: salabat(ginger tea)
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
(The longer it cooks, the stronger the ginger flavor.) Remove ginger slice before serving.
Serve hot.

title: maple monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine syrup and melted butter in a saucepan and mix well.
Heat until bubbly.
Add nuts to this mixture.
Separate breadsticks by slicing rolled dough in half. Combine the sugar and cinnamon.
Generously grease a tube pan or a bread pan.
Pour a small amount of syrup mixture into bottom of pan (enough to cover bottom).
Dip pieces of dough into remaining syrup mixture, coating well, then roll in the cinnamon sugar and place in the tube pan.
Pour remaining syrup mixture on top of dough.
Bake about 35 minutes or until dough is light brown, covering with foil for the last 10 minutes to prevent overbrowning.
Let stand 1 minute only.
Invert onto a serving platter.
Serve warm.

title: banana foster
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar and cream of coconut; bring to a boil.
Boil until thick and squeeze juice of one orange into mixture.
Dice banana and put in mixture.
Toss.
Serve over vanilla ice cream by each serving.

title: hot crab appetizers
directions: Melt margarine and cheese in small saucepan.
Stir in crab, green pepper and onion, if desired.
Spread a tablespoon or so on each bun half.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients
together
and
crumble
saltine or Ritz crackers and butter on top.
Cook at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Cook onion in bacon fat.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed, and pepper. Add water and vinegar.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add potatoes, bacon and eggs.
Heat thoroughly.
Garnish with pimiento and/or parsley.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, stir well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake in a well greased pan (9 x 13-inch) at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: u-know pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add melted chocolate chips; stir well.
Add one egg and beat 5 minutes at medium speed.
Add the second egg, and beat 5 minutes. Add vanilla and mix well. Pour into a baked and cooled pie shell or graham cracker crust. Chill 4-8 hours.

title: curried cabbage
directions: Wash the cabbage and shred as for slaw.
Heat butter in a large skillet.
Add the garlic, curry powder and salt; saute for about 2 minutes.
Add the cabbage; cook, covered, until tender, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Some cooks like to add a cup of canned tomatoes just before the cabbage is done.
If it seems to stick during cooking, add just a little water.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble corn bread in a large bowl; chop onions, radishes, green peppers and tomatoes.
Add to cornbread, combine mayonnaise, dressing and mustard.
Toss lightly in cornbread; add salt.

title: tomato aspic(stagecoach inn, salado, texas)
directions: Put the first 8 ingredients in pan and simmer for a long time; do not boil.
Mix next 5 ingredients well; then strain hot mixture into cold, stirring constantly.
Pour into tray and sprinkle with finely minced onion.
This makes such a large recipe; share it with your neighbors.

title: fried baked apples
directions: First, cut apples, then put tablespoon of water, then tablespoon of sugar and tablespoon of cinnamon.
Put in microwave for 5 minutes.

title: mexican soup
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Once browned, drain grease and combine all ingredients into large stewer and cook for 30 minutes or until thoroughly hot.

title: filled oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook filling until thickened and cool (raisins, sugar, water, 2 tablespoons flour and walnuts).
Mix together oats, 2 cups flour, baking soda and salt in one bowl.
Mix together brown sugar, melted oleo and vanilla in another bowl.
Combine the two mixtures.
Work with fingers until well mixed.
Put half mixture in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pat firmly.
Put cooked filling on top.
Top with other half of mixture.
Pat firmly.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine biscuit mix, 3 tablespoons sugar, 3 tablespoons butter and the milk, mixing with a fork to form a soft dough.
Knead dough on a lightly floured board; roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 12 (3-inch) rounds.
Brush 6 of the rounds with the 2 tablespoons of butter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Top with remaining rounds and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix and place in deep casserole dish.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Tear cake into 1-inch pieces, layer 1/2 of cake pieces, yogurt, topping, strawberries and kiwi in a two-quart bowl; repeat.
Refrigerate about 2 hours or until firm.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir flour, soda and salt together.
In a mixer bowl, beat butter and shortening on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture; beat until combined.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: cherry kuchen
directions: Combine milk, sugar and farina, stirring frequently.
Heat until thickened just to boiling point; don't boil.
Let mixture cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks into cooled milk-farina-sugar mixture.
Add cherries, almonds or hazelnuts, butter and cinnamon to mixture.
Add egg whites to mixture.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with cream or whipped cream.

title: baked fish a l'orange
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Thaw fish, if frozen.
Arrange in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook onion and garlic in oil until onion is tender, but not brown.
Stir in parsley, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Spread mixture over fish.
Combine orange and lemon juices; pour evenly over all.

title: chocolate wax candy
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
When cool, shape into bars or into balls.
Dip into the following, melted over low heat:

title: stuffed party mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brush or wipe mushrooms clean.
Remove stems and set caps aside.
Finely chop mushroom stems.
In medium bowl, combine chopped stems and all remaining ingredients.
Press mixture firmly into caps, mounding on top.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 23 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: best rice ever
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Combine all ingredients and marinate overnight.
Drain if needed.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Place sourdough starter in large bowl.
Sift in baking powder, soda and salt.
Add vegetable oil and mix well.
Flour board with 1/2 cup flour and put remaining flour into sifter.
Gradually add flour from sifter, and blend after each addition.
When mixture begins to hold together well, grease hands and turn mixture out onto board.
As you add remaining flour, knead it in a rhythmic fashion.

title: winter salad
directions: Shake vinegar and sugar in jar until dissolved.
Add mayo and shake until blended.
Pour over broccoli at serving time.
Sprinkle sunflower seeds on top.

title: yellow cucumber pickles
directions: Peel cucumbers; scrape out seeds.
Cut cucumbers, onion and celery in small cubes.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 2 hours; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.

title: coconut pound cake ii
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Stir in with a spoon, vanilla flavoring, wafer crumbs, coconut and walnuts.
Grease and lightly flour tube pan.
Pour ingredients into pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°. Let cool 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Place broccoli in a 9-inch pie plate sprayed with cooking spray. Sprinkle with green pepper, onion and cheese.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in blender; blend for 15 seconds or until smooth.
Pour over broccoli mixture; bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: strawberries and cream dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and water.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 2 cups pudding mixture into 4-quart glass serving bowl.
Top with half each of the cake cubes, sliced strawberries, preserves and remaining pudding.
Repeat layering, ending with pudding.
Garnish with strawberries and almonds.
Chill thoroughly.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mock chicken kiev
directions: Mash margarine with garlic, parsley and chives.
Divide into 2 equal portions and refrigerate until chilled.
Place chicken breasts between two sheets of waxed paper and pound with mallet until 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place herbed butter in center of each chicken breast, tuck in sides and roll up breast and fasten with toothpicks.
Heat oil in skillet.
Brown breasts quickly until golden.
Place in lightly greased ovenware and bake in 350° oven 1/2 hour or until chicken is done.
Serve with rice or noodles, a vegetable and tossed salad.
Serves two; 154 calories.

title: buster bars
directions: Combine melted margarine with crushed Oreos and pat into 9X13 pan.
Freeze.
Soften ice cream and spread onto crust.
Sprinkle with half the peanuts and freeze.
Bring sugar, milk, margarine and chocolate chips to a boil; cook until thickened.
Allow to cool.
Spread on top of ice cream.
Top with remaining peanuts and freeze.
Cut into squares to serve.
Store in freezer.

title: pecan crescents
directions: In a large bowl, beat butter, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add pecans; mix until blended.
Wrap dough. Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 300°.
Divide dough into 8 equal pieces.
On lightly floured board, roll each piece into a 12 3/4-inch long rope.
Cut each rope into 8 pieces.
Shape into crescents.
Place one inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes, or just until golden.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Grind the cranberries and orange.
Add the sugar.
Mix well and let stand overnight.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups warm water. When slightly thickened, add to cranberry mixture.
Add nuts, celery and apples.
Pour into mold and refrigerate until set.

title: spiced maple cider
directions: In large saucepan combine all ingredients except liquor; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Remove orange slices and spices.
Add liquor, if desired.
Serve warm, or chill and add 2 liter bottle ginger ale just before serving.

title: green creole beans
directions: Saute in olive oil the onion, pepper and celery for 3 minutes. Mix in tomatoes and beans.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until vegetables are heated through.

title: easy minestrone
directions: In Dutch oven, over medium heat, heat oil.
Add garlic, celery, carrots and onion; cook 10 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in broth, tomatoes and their liquids, water, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, breaking up tomatoes with spoon.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in beans and macaroni.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes longer.
Stir in spinach.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes longer. Serve sprinkled with cheese.

title: preserved children
directions: Mix the children and dogs together; put them in field, stirring constantly.
Pour the brook over the pebbles; sprinkle the field with flowers.
Spread deep blue sky over all and bake in sunshine.
When brown, set away to cool in the bathtub.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: Pour rice into flat baking dish.
Brown pork chops in skillet.
Place in baking dish on top of rice.
Salt lightly. Place on top of each pork chop in stacked fashion one slice each of onion, tomato and green pepper.
Sprinkle with oregano, thyme and salt.
Pour into used skillet the consomme and water.
Add this to baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except raisins and dates.
Toss well to coat evenly with apple juice.
Spread on nonstick baking sheet.
Bake until golden brown, stirring every 30 minutes for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
After granola is cooled, remove from baking sheet and add dates and raisins.
Store in cool place in airtight container.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar gradually.
Beat until fluffy. Add eggs and continue to beat.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Add soda to boiling water. Stir into rest of ingredients.
This makes a thin batter.
Pour into two 8-inch pans which have been greased.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: french beef au gratin
directions: In large, heavy-bottomed pan over medium heat, melt I Can't Believe Its Not Butter!
Add onions; saute, stirring often, until caramelized but not burned, 15 to 20 minutes.
With slotted spoon remove onions to medium bowl.
Add beef to pan; brown well on all sides.
Return onions and any juices to pan.
In small bowl, mix flour, sugar, cumin, salt and pepper.
Add to pan; stir 1 minute until bubbly.
Gradually add broth, stirring to scrape drippings from pan.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Heat broiler.
Place 1/2 cup fettuccine in each of 4 (about 16 ounce) ovenproof bowls; divide beef mixture over pasta.

title: creamy carrot-nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add yogurt and stir until well blended.
Stir in pineapple, carrots, pecans and salt. Spoon into lightly oiled mold or cake pan.
Cover and chill until firm.
Yield: 9 servings.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Quarter
cabbage
and
shred
firmly.
Put
cabbage and pickling
salt in large pan.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Pack into
a
crock or a gallon glass jar, pressing it down firmly. Add sprigs
of dill or dill seed.
Repeat until crock is full or until you have the desired amount.
Cover it with a cloth, plate and weight.
Remove scum as it forms and wash and scald cloth before using again.
Fermentation will be complete in 10 to 15 days.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and process until completely smooth. Spoon into bowls and chill before serving.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix together.
Roll between wax paper.
No flour is needed. Makes 2 crusts.

title: zesty italian crescent casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In frypan, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Heat until hot and bubbly.
Combine cheese and sour cream.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef in frypan.
Remove beef from pan, reserving drippings. Dilute tomato paste with 2 cups water.
Add salt. Mix rice, meat, onion, green pepper and tomato mixture together. Pour in 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 10 servings.

title: pumpkin bread puddings
directions: In a bowl, whisk together the brown sugar, the cinnamon, the nutmeg, the cream, the milk, the pumpkin, the raisins, the egg, the vanilla and a pinch of salt until the mixture is smooth.
Stir in the bread cubes and let the mixture stand for 5 minutes.
Divide the mixture between 2 buttered 1-cup microwave-safe ramekins fitted with wax paper collars extending 2 inches above the rim.
Microwave the puddings at High power (100%), switching positions once, for 15 to 17 minutes, or until a tester comes out clean.
Let them stand for 3 minutes.
Discard the paper collars and serve with puddings warm.
Serves 2.

title: porcupines
directions: Combine ground chuck, rice, salt and pepper in bowl and mix well.
Roll meat mixture into small balls.
Pour tomato juice into large boiler; bring to boil.
Add meat balls and cook on low heat until rice is done.
Stir frequently; serve with crackers.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: You can also use pork chops or wieners.

title: jello refrigerator pies
directions: Mix Carnation milk and sugar; whip until stands in peaks. Combine Jell-O, pineapple, undrained and sugar.
Heat until boiling.
Cool to lukewarm.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put in 2 pie pans lined with vanilla wafers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mexico chili
directions: Place chili meat in a large frying pan or heavy kettle.
Keep flame low and sear meat slowly, until juices appear.
Add garlic, onion, celery, comino seed and chili powder.
Continue to cook for about 15 minutes.
Turn meat slowly.
Put in a large kettle.
Add tomato juice, red chili, oregano, water and salt and pepper to taste.
Let come to a boil.
Cut heat down to a simmer and cook until meat is tender, approximately 2 to 3 hours.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Mix together and bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: applesauce fudge squares
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Cool slightly.
Add sugar, eggs, applesauce and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool, then sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan macaroni, then cheese, several layers with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes until bubbly and lightly browned.
Serve.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Combine
water,
shortening,
margarine
and cocoa in a medium saucepan.	Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture comes
to
a
boil. Combine flour and sugar in a large mixing
bowl. Add cocoa mixture, stirring well.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Pour batter into a greased and floured 13	x
x
1/4-inch
pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or	until
done.
Cool
cake in pan completely. Spread Chocolate Nut Frosting on top.

title: chocolate-peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan over medium heat. Bring to boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients; stir until chocolate chips are melted. Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: mexican potatoes
directions: Wash, then cut unpeeled potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Place in bowl.
Add oil; mix to coat.
Put chili powder and cumin in bag and add potatoes; shake to mix well.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
When serving, pour melted cheese over each serving.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well; roll into balls.
Chill well.
Melt milk chocolate and paraffin over hot water.
Stick toothpicks into candy balls and dip in chocolate.
Lay on wax paper.

title: corn relish
directions: Boil corn for 5 minutes.
Cut from cob.
Combine with remaining ingredients in a large saucepot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Pack hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch head space.
Adjust caps.
Process for 15 minutes in boiling water bath. Yields about 6 pints.

title: strawberry-jello salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water (2 cups only).
Add strawberries with liquid; add bananas, pineapple and nuts.
Pour half of this in pan and cool until thick.
Spread sour cream on top, add remaining mixture on top.
Let chill.

title: real italian meatballs
directions: Soak bread in water 2 or 3 minutes.
Add 2 eggs and mix well. Mix in ground beef, cheese, parsley, dash of pepper, oregano and dash of salt.
With wet hands, form into small balls (about 24). Brown slowly in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil.
Add meatballs to your favorite sauce.

title: gay's chile rellenos
directions: Split chiles and remove seeds and veins.
Cut Jack cheese into 1/4-inch strips to fit inside chile.
Fold chile over cheese. Mix Bisquick, sausage and cheese.
(May need to add a tablespoon or so of milk.)
Take sausage mixture and form it completely around green chile.
Press in hands so that mixture adheres completely to chile.
(Add toothpicks to hold together.)
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and water.
Add relish and pineapple; set. Then cover with 1 carton sour cream mixed with miniature marshmallows.
Also can top with 1 package cream cheese and 1 package Dream Whip or just put a little Cool Whip on it.
Serves 15.

title: nanny's oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat eggs together and add other ingredients in order given, mixing with each item thoroughly as added.
Batter will be very stiff.
Drop by spoonful on greased tins and bake at 350°.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt butter and blend with crumbs.
Combine cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Mix Dream Whip with milk as directed on box. Put layer of crumb mixture, layer of cream cheese and layer of cherry pie filling.
Repeat and end with pie filling.
Put Dream Whip over cake.
Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Butter tube pan; put in raisins and/or nuts.
Roll frozen rolls in cinnamon and arrange them in a single ring solid in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle one package vanilla pudding mix dry over rolls. Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar, dribble 1/2 cup melted butter.
Cover with towel and let set overnight or at least 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel chocolate squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat caramels and 1/4 cup milk over medium heat, stirring constantly until melted and smooth; keep mixture warm over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: carlotta's taco soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion.
Put meat and onion mixture into a slow cooker. Add the remaining ingredients and simmer on low for 2-3 hours.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook over medium heat for 3 minutes (start timing when mixture starts to boil).
Remove from heat and stir in oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix this well before it gets hard.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper and let cool. Makes about 24 cookies.

title: quick chocolate brittle
directions: Lightly grease 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle peanuts into pan and set aside.
Combine brown sugar and butter in medium saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 270° on candy thermometer.
Immediately pour over peanuts in pan. Sprinkle chocolate morsels over top.
Cover with aluminum foil for 2 minutes.
Remove foil and spread melted chocolate over top. Chill until firm.
Remove candy from pan and break into pieces.

title: dirty rice(cajun dish)
directions: Melt oil in heavy pan and cook chicken if not using already cooked chicken, about 6 minutes, stirring constantly. Drain fat. Stir in Cajun Spice, onion, celery, pepper and garlic.
Add margarine and chicken stock and cook about 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Add rice. Cover pan and simmer about 8 minutes until rice is hot.

title: chocolate wine cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips in large bowl with electric mixer for 5 minutes.
Fold in chips with spoon.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let stand for 10 minutes.
Invert and let cool 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: 2nd only to sex cake
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts; press into an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cream together the cream cheese, powdered sugar, salt and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix puddings, milk, sour cream and vanilla.
Spread over top of cake.
Chill 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll crescent dough into one big rectangle and press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry Ranch dressing until blended.
Spread over dough.
Top with vegetables and cheese.
Cut into squares, 2 x 2-inches, to serve.

title: country grits and sausage
directions: Bring water and salt to boil.
Add grits and return to boil. Reduce heat.
Cook 4 minutes.
Melt in cheese.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Saute garlic, green pepper, mushrooms and onion in oil. Combine with all ingredients, except zucchini, and heat through. Add zucchini and heat to desired tenderness.
Serve topped with a small amount of shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: caramel nut crunch pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix crushed cookies, peanuts and melted butter in 9 x 11 plate, using fork; press firmly and evenly over bottom and up sides of plate. Bake 10 minutes; cool completely before filling.

title: brandy fruit sauce
directions: Cut
up
apples,
pears
and nectarines.
Pour mix over fruit and marinate 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator or overnight.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: Cook cauliflower covered in salted water until
crispy tender. Drain and place in shallow six cup baking dish.
Mix cheeses and crumbs in a small bowl.
Drizzle margarine over top of cheese mixture and toss to coat crumbs.
Sprinkle over the cauliflower. Bake uncovered at 425° for 10 minutes or until topping is golden brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook
carrots
in
salty water until tender.
Drain and add onion,
pepper
and other ingredients and heat, then cool. Serve hot or cold.
Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: fudgy brownie pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Coat 9-inch square pan with Pam vegetable spray. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and 1/3 cup cocoa in medium bowl. Combine skim milk, melted oleo and vanilla in measuring cup and stir into dry ingredients. Spoon batter into prepared pan. Combine brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa in small bowl. Sprinkle over batter. Pour boiling water over top. Do not stir! Bake 35 minutes until tested done in center. Cool 10 minutes. Serve warm.

title: old-time corn fritters
directions: Mix ingredients together in the order given, adding just enough flour to hold fritters together.
Drop by tablespoon in hot fat; cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Melt butter and add other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Mold into fingers and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; let cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: lemon sherbet
directions: Add sugar to warmed milk and stir until dissolved, then add lemon juice, rind and salt.
Soak gelatin in the cold water for 5 minutes, place over boiling water and heat until gelatin is dissolved, while stirring.
Then add to first mixture while stirring.
Pour into the freezing tray of refrigerator with temperature control at coldest setting, and freeze until firm, about 1 inch in from edge of tray.
Stir and whip with a fork until smooth.
Freeze until firm.
A half hour before serving, stir and whip again with a fork until smooth.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all together with the salad dressing. Add more if desired.

title: fine crumb pie shell
directions: Combine crumbs with melted margarine and water.
Add sugar replacement, if desired.
Spread dough evenly in 8 to 10-inch pan, pressing firmly onto sides and bottom.
Either chill until set or bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: something good pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, pecans and nuts. Spread mixture on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, 1 carton of whipped topping and vanilla, mixing well.
Spread over cooled crust.
Combine pudding mix and milk.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining carton of whipped topping.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cornstarch) well.
Shape into meatballs the size of walnuts.
Roll meatballs in cornstarch.
Fry for 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Add tomatoes, sugar, mustard, ketchup, salt, pepper and spices.
Melt cheese in sauce near end of cooking.
Cook on medium low to desired thickness.

title: apple walnut spice cake
directions: Peel, core and thinly slice apples and line bottom of
9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle walnuts over the top of the apples. Prepare a spice cake mix according to directions and pour over the apple-walnut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Cool.
Cover.
Set for 24 hours.
Then serve.
Very moist.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Let cream cheese and butter sit at room temperature.
Beat well; add sugar and eggs and beat well.
Sift in flour and mix; add flavorings.
Bake in Bundt pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool and use your own glaze.

title: baked pears a-la-mode
directions: Blend sugar, flour, and salt. Combine with margarine in a small pan. Add pineapple juice and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Pour the mixture over pears in an oblong baking dish and bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients.
Shape into balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: walleye pike izaty's style
directions: Divide flour into 1 cup portions in 2 separate pans.
Into 1 portion, mix cornmeal, paprika and salt.
Set both pans aside.
In another shallow bowl, beat eggs and add milk.
One at a time, dip fillets into pan of plain flour, then into egg mixture, again into plain flour and then in cornmeal mixture.
Fry in heated shortening until brown.

title: lemon sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs. Add vanilla and lemon extract and mix; add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes in preheated oven.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter in double boiler.
Add shoestring potatoes and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Makes about 24.

title: homemade bread
directions: In a large bowl, make batter of ingredients.
Grease another bowl; put dough in, turning over lightly once.
Cover tightly with foil and let set overnight.
Do not put in refrigerator.
Push down and divide into 3 parts.
Knead each part 8 to 10 times.
Put in greased loaf pans.
Cover with Saran Wrap and let rise all day. Bread rises slowly.
Start with cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and brush with butter.
Let cool and wrap.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: tasty beef dish(easy)
directions: Brown meat.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Pour off excess drippings.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Stir in ingredients.
Re-cover and simmer for at least 1 more hour, or until tender.
Stir from time to time.
Add more liquid if it starts to dry out.
Serves 6.

title: round steak sauerbraten
directions: Brown meat in oil; remove meat.
Add 2 cups water and gravy mix.
Simmer to boil.
Add onion, sugar, salt and pepper, ginger, Worcestershire and bay leaf.
Simmer.
Add meat and simmer for 1 hour.
Pour over cooked noodles.

title: 15 minute beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in frying pan and add water, chicken soup and onion soup; mix.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Blend flour and sour cream and add to meat.
Stir until thick.
Heat to boiling but do not boil.
Serve on rice or noodles.

title: toffee butter crunch
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Add sugar, water and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, to exactly 290°.
Remove from heat.
Immediately turn into a buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Wait 2 to 3 minutes or until firm and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
After chocolate is softened, spread evenly over toffee.
Chill until chocolate is firm.
Break into pieces and enjoy.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Heat bacon fat in 10-inch skillet.
Add cabbage.
Cook over low heat until brown.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Red cabbage may be fixed the same way.

title: easiest ever dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 13 x 9 baking pan. Dump pineapple and juice into pan. Dump in pie filling. Spread evenly. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over cherry layer. Sprinkle pecans over cake mix. Dot with slices of butter. Bake for 50 minutes or until top is lightly browned. Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Blend in
dry
ingredients; reserve 4 tablespoons flour to dust fruit.
Beat in milk, vanilla and almond extract until smooth. Combine cherries,
raisins,
dates,
nuts and coconut with the reserved flour.
Fold
into
cake
batter.	Bake in a greased and floured cake mold or loaf type bread pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours or
until
a	cake
tester inserted comes out clean. Sprinkle cake with your choice of liquor.

title: beet pickles
directions: Boil beets until tender and skins will slip off easily.
Pour off water.
Run cold water on and slip off skins.
Bring vinegar, sugar, water and allspice to a boil.
Put beets in jars; pour boiling liquid over and seal jars.
Wait a few days before eating them.

title: broccoli bars
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Add cheese and broccoli. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
Let cool slightly before cutting.
(Chopped spinach can be substituted for broccoli.)

title: apple butter nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pan.

title: whoopee pies
