directions: Combine all ingredients until just moistened. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes until light and thick. Drop by heaping tablespoons onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 15 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes on racks.

title: et-too-fay
directions: Mix soups, tomato sauce, Ro-Tel and water.
Add crawfish and cook 20 minutes at low temperature.
Add 1 pound Velveeta cheese. Cook 10 minutes.
Pour this over cooked rice and serve with cornbread.

title: rhubarb custard cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Mix rhubarb and sugar.
Put on top of cake.
Pour whipping cream over this (not whipped).
Cool.
When serving, tip upside down and the custard will be on top.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour and pecans.
Press firmly into long shallow dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked beans with ground beef
directions: Brown ground beef.
Alternate layers, ending with beans, onions, sugar, mustard and catsup.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: steak oriental
directions: Cut meat into small pieces; brown.
Add carrots, green pepper and onion.
In 2-cup measuring pitcher, combine mushroom gravy and teriyaki sauce; pour over vegetables.
Cook on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until vegies are somewhat tender.

title: artichoke bread
directions: Melt butter over medium-high heat in a large skillet.
Add garlic and sesame seed.
Stir constantly until lightly browned. Remove from heat and stir in artichokes and next 3 ingredients. Mix may be refrigerated up to 24 hours.
Bring to room temperature before assembling.
Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Scoop out center of each half leaving a 1-inch shell.
Set aside.

title: cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Melt almond bark coating in top of double boiler.
Pour over mixture and toss until well coated.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper to cool.

title: fantastic salad
directions: Mix dry jello and cottage cheese.
Stir in drained fruit and fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
In separate bowl, beat whipping cream until thick.
In a large bowl (third), beat egg yolks with sugar and add liquors.
Add half and half, egg whites and whipping cream and stir gently until well blended.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
If too thick, add more half and half.
Can cut down on whiskey or omit as tastes dictate.
Also can substitute milk for half and half to cut down on fat.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican dish
directions: Layer in baking dish beans, salsa, olives and cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts through.
Serve topped with sour cream.

title: "spanakopita" (without filo) - spinach pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and put the American cheese on top.
Bake until golden brown in 15 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch pan in 400° oven.

title: magic cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.

title: cake cones
directions: Make cake mix as directed and place 2 Tbsp. batter in each cone (1/2 full).

title: my lemon pie
directions: Mix together the lemon peel, juice, flour and butter.
Beat smooth.
Add milk, sugar and egg yolks until blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff and peaks form.
Fold into egg yolk mixture. Pour into crust.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.
Serve chilled. Cover and refrigerate up to 2 days.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Mix onions, potatoes, carrots and 1/2 teaspoon salt and cook for 10 minutes in 3 cups boiling water; drain off liquid and save for gravy.
Brown chicken in butter; add wine, cream, vegetables, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes until chicken is tender; place chicken in center of dish with vegetables around.
Make gravy from liquid saved off of vegetables; cook until thick.
Serve with Minute rice.
(I add the vegetables to the chicken and then pour the white wine and milk over it all.)

title: super shrimp dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender or food processor; blend well.
Keep cool until ready to serve.
Good with any kind of chips or party crackers.

title: coconut pudding cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on the box.
Pour batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake.
Mix coconut milk and instant pudding on high for 2 minutes or until lumps are dissolved.
Use pudding mixture as icing for cake.
Spread Cool Whip over icing, then sprinkle with shredded coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix rice and ground beef in a large bowl.
Form meatballs and roll each ball in rice.
Place in a large pot.
Pour tomato sauce over the meatballs and simmer for 45 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: no knead cinnamon or caramel rolls
directions: Mix together; roll out as you would other rolls and prepare them for the pans.
Let rise until doubled and then bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil fryer until tender and debone. Cook rice in 2 1/2 cups plus 2 tablespoons chicken broth.
(Bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.)
Add chopped onion to rice and cook for 5 minutes.
Combine chicken, rice and all other ingredients; mix well.
Bake in large, buttered casserole dish for 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and then add all other ingredients together in a bowl.
Using a rubber spatula (do not use electric mixer) combine just until mixed.
Place in bread pan, lightly greased.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: green beans caesar
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toss beans with salad oil, vinegar, onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Stir together the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and butter.
Sprinkle over beans.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: pasta with vodka sauce
directions: Heat water for pasta and cook according to package directions. Heat olive oil in a medium saucepan and saute chile peppers over low heat for 30 seconds.
Add vodka (mixture will splatter); raise heat and cook 30 seconds.
Stir in tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat, stir in cream, salt and pepper and cook 5 minutes. Do not let sauce boil.
When pasta is ready; drain well.
Place in serving bowl and add half the sauce.
Mix well and top with remaining sauce.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with green peppers, onion and celery.
Cook macaroni according to package instructions; drain.
Mix all ingredients together, cutting cheese into small chunks.
Place bacon on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts or bread and arrange 8 slices in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay slices of meat and cheese on bread and top with remaining slices of bread.
Beat together the eggs, salt, onion salt, dry mustard and milk.
Pour over sandwiches and refrigerate overnight.
Make a topping of corn flakes and butter and spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add the seasoning.
Mix well. Will keep two weeks in refrigerator. Better than Ranch.

title: trish's cucumber tea sandwiches
directions: Mix sour cream, mayo and cream cheese until smooth.
Add dill weed and mix.
Spread mixture on each slice of bread; top with sliced cucumber.
Sprinkle with additional dill weed.
Serve immediately.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and brown sugar until fluffy; add beaten eggs and sifted dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and salad dressing together.
Add fruit cocktail and nuts.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream and place in freezer compartment.
When ready to serve, slice and place on lettuce leaf.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Add to cooked potatoes and hard-boiled eggs.
No green pepper or celery.

title: baked beans
directions: Use bacon drippings to saute onion in a medium frypan.
Add beans, then mustard, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Cook slowly about 10 minutes.
Place in dish and place bacon on top.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and oleo.
Press 1/2 mixture in long deep pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Mix 1 cup milk with 1 package instant pistachio pudding.
Stir until thick.
Add cherries and nuts.
Whip 1 package Dream Whip.
Fold into pudding mixture. Spread on cooled crust.
Sprinkle reserved graham mixture on top of this layer.
Mix 1 package vanilla or pineapple instant pudding mix with 1 cup milk until thick.
Add pineapple and coconut.
Whip 1 package Dream Whip.
Add to pudding mix and spread over pistachio layer.
Sprinkle coconut, nuts and cherries on top, if desired.

title: old fashion soft sugar cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar, then add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla or nutmeg and sifted dry ingredients.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry beef, chopped onion, chopped green pepper and chili powder until beef is browned.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: meat sauce for pasta
directions: Heat oil.
Add only meat and brown slightly.
Break into small pieces with fork.
Add onions and garlic.
Heat gently until wilted and tender.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasoning; simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Arrange cooked pasta on plates and pour sauce over pasta.

title: orange and honey-roasted pork tenderloin(serves 6)
directions: Set pork on platter.
Using fork, work orange peel, thyme, pepper and garlic to paste in small bowl.
Rub into pork.
Combine orange juice and vinegar in same bowl.
Pour over pork.
Cover pork and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: bunky's quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch pan.
Pour peaches in pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: fried-up okra
directions: Rinse the okra.
Remove the caps.
Cut into 1/4-inch pieces. Mix cornmeal, flour and salt.
Toss the okra with mixture.
Spread out for a few minutes to dry.
Toss again.
Fill skillet halfway with oil.
Heat to sizzling.
Add okra.
Leave enough room to turn.
Fry until lightly browned, turning only to prevent burning. Add salt and pepper while still hot.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with crackers.
For extra tang, add more horseradish.

title: peas and cheese
directions: Blend together the first 4 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Marinate 4 hours (best overnight).
Serve on shredded lettuce. Baby shrimp or thinly sliced radishes may be added for variety.

title: hamburger-tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet and add spices.
Stir in cheese soup.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Top mixture with layer of Tater Tots and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: crock-pot country ribs
directions: Cut ribs apart and place in crock-pot.
Stir all other ingredients together and pour over ribs.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours.
Serve with noodles and green veggies!

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix flour,
oleo
and
powdered
sugar and press in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake	for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Next, mix egg yolks,
rhubarb, flour, sugar and milk and cook until thick.
Put on top of baked crust.
Beat egg whites and put on top and bake until brown.

title: baked cod fillets
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until golden.
Add other ingredients, except for fish.
Simmer covered for 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut fillets into serving pieces and put in a greased baking dish.
Pour sauce over fish.
Bake for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix fat, sugar and eggs.
Stir in vanilla.
Mix in baking soda, salt and flour.
Mix in oats and raisins.
Drop dough by spoonfuls on baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix marinade ingredients and marinate steak for 6 to 7 hours. Cook for 6 minutes per side. Slice thin in diagonal strips.

title: not so sour kraut
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Mix red wine vinegar and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Mix chopped vegetables.
Pour boiling liquid over vegetables and toss.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine all vegetables in large pan and sprinkle with salt. Cover with cold water.
Let stand 4 hours.
Drain; press out excess liquid.

title: pizza dip or sauce
directions: Heat soup.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve with apples, celery, pepper, broccoli, cauliflower, Italian or French bread cubes for dipping or as a sauce over potatoes, broccoli and cauliflower.

title: turkey sour cream patties
directions: In a medium size bowl, mix turkey, 1/2 cup bread crumbs, sour cream, milk, pepper and nutmeg.
Shape into 4 flat patties.
Coat on both sides with remaining crumbs.
Set on rack and refrigerate for 20 minutes.
Lightly coat a heavy 10-inch skillet with cooking spray and margarine; set over moderate heat.
Add patties and brown 5 minutes on each side.
Transfer to heated platter and serve.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in whipped topping and half of crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies in bottom of cup.
Fill cups 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Decorate.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, melted butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour batter into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In small bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over batter.
Pour hot water over top.
Do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Spoon into dessert dishes, spooning sauce from bottom of pan over top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop the onions and cut beef into little cubes.
Combine all ingredients and work together into ball.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving with your favorite cracker.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour.
Fry slowly in oil until brown.	Remove from pan.
Pour off excess oil leaving a little to make gravy.
Fry onion in remaining oil until wilted.
Pour boiling water into onion.
Add chops to onion and water.
Cover and simmer until tender.

title: donna's homemade pimento and cheese
directions: Heat cheese and milk in double boiler and add vinegar, sugar, pimento, salt and egg.
Cook this for 15 minutes and take off stove.
Add mayo with electric mixer.
Keeps up to one month in refrigerator.
For a more cheesy taste, don't use a whole pint of mayo.

title: basil butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl; mix well.

title: beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper in a large skillet.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Simmer 15 minutes. Separate each biscuit into 2 layers.
Place 10 layers over bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch baking dish.
Mix well 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream and egg.
Remove meat mixture from heat; stir in cream mixture and spoon over dough.
Arrange other biscuit layers on top. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are deep golden brown.

title: raisin puff cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water until water is gone, then cool.
Put sugar in bowl and pour oil on top and mix.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix.
Mix dry ingredients, then add to oil mixture.
Add raisins.
This must be chilled well.
(Overnight or all day is recommended.)
Roll into balls and dip in granulated sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 15 minutes.
These keep well if they last long enough!

title: concord grape pie
directions: Slip skins from washed, stemmed grapes.
Boil pulp 5 minutes. Rub through sieve to remove seeds.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt and rind with pulp.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add grape skins; cool.
Turn into pie shell.
Cover with lattice top strips.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 20 minutes more.

title: lemon gelatin cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and gelatin.
Add water, salad oil and eggs one at a time.
Beat 1 minute.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Have ready when cake is done the powdered sugar and lemon juice, which has been thoroughly mixed.
Puncture the top of the cake with a large fork all over the top.
Pour the sugar and lemon juice mixture all over the cake while it is hot from the oven so the mixture is absorbed into the cake.
Serves 12 to 16.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: coconut pie
directions: Put in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy chops
directions: Crush Better Cheddars until fine. Wash chops in cool water. Place about 3/4
cup finely crushed crackers in plastic bag. Place one chop at a time in plastic bag with crackers and shake until coated well.
Place in baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle lightly with pepper and bake at 350° until pork is done.

title: crazy cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Add oil, vinegar, vanilla and water; beat until smooth.
Pour cake batter into a small cake pan (8 x 8-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fingerpaint(kids stuff)
directions: Whip flakes with enough water to form a slightly thick mixture.
Add a drop of food coloring.

title: ladybug salad
directions: Pound Cake:
Begin with pound cake.
Pile on chocolate or butterscotch pudding.
Add on blueberries, raspberries or strawberries.
Sprinkle on walnuts, pecans or almonds.

title: easter morning breakfast
directions: Brown the sausage; drain.
Add the other ingredients.
Bake in an 8 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
This may be mixed and put in the refrigerator overnight if using for breakfast. Serves 6.

title: ground beef and vegetables
directions: Cook the beef and drain fat.
Peel potatoes and cut in chunks. Add onions or garlic.
Cut cabbage in pieces.
Add carrots, peeled and sliced.
Add green beans.
Cook until about done.
Add the catsup and finish cooking with pan covered.

title: creamy pineapple dessert
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add water to juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Combine pudding mix, gelatin and measured liquid in medium saucepan.
Cook, stirring, over medium heat until mixture comes to full boil.
Pour into a bowl; chill until thickened. Fold thawed topping into pudding mixture.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a large bowl. Mix well and place in a loaf pan. Bake 3 hours at 400°.

title: baked barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in shallow pan.
Bake for 2 hours at 275°.

title: microwave basic white sauce
directions: Heat milk in glass measure on 70 (roast) 2 minutes.
Set aside, melt butter on High for 45 seconds.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Cook on High 1 minute.
Briskly stir in warm milk. Cook on High 3 to 4 minutes or until boiling, stirring once during cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serve on cooked vegetables or as a base for other sauces.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix butter, shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly. Add dry ingredients, mix until the dough
is firm enough to handle. This can be used in a cookie press or rolled out and cut with cookie cutters. Decorate with powdered sugar frosting.

title: brandy slush
directions: Bring 7 cups water and 2 cups sugar to a boil and let cool.
In a bowl, pour the 2 cups boiling water over the tea bags.
Let cool and pour over the first mixture.
Add the lemonade, orange juice and brandy.
Mix all together and freeze.
Stir after 12 hours to prevent separating.

title: summer goulash
directions: Prepare all vegetables.
Heat oil in Dutch oven and add vegetables.
Stir vegetables to coat well with oil.
Add to this 1 cup water and 1/2 stick margarine.
Cover and cook on medium heat until vegetables are tender, adding more water as needed.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.

title: cinnamon pecan coffee cake
directions: Mix
cake
mix, vanilla pudding, eggs, Crisco and water together; set aside.
Combine white sugar, brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle this sugar mixture in bottom of greased
9	x
13-inch pan.
Pour thin layer of batter over this and
then
another	layer
of
sugar.
Follow
by adding remaining batter
and
remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 4 minutes.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Melt oleo and mix in flour and nuts.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown. Cool.

title: baked fish with sour cream
directions: Cut fish in serving pieces.
Pat dry.
Cook onion in margarine for 3 minutes.
Place fish in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Spread onion over top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix sour cream and cheese.
Spread over fish.
Sprinkle crumbs over top. Bake uncovered 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and paprika before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mike's ham bone soup
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer for flavor.
Can add any vegetables you like.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix and add Kraft French dressing and a dash of Tabasco.

title: spinach salad with oranges and peanuts
directions: Clean spinach.
Stem and tear into bite-size pieces.
If using oranges, peel, pith and section.
Crush peanuts in plastic bag with rolling pin.
Fry bacon and then crumble into small pieces. When ready to serve, combine all ingredients in
a large glass bowl.
Toss with Catalina dressing, just enough to coat spinach. Serve at once.

title: hungarian beef and noodles
directions: Cook noodles; drain and reserve.
Cook ground beef and onion in large skillet over medium heat, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon and toss with noodles.
Drain fat from skillet and heat water and margarine to boiling; add cabbage and cook and stir until cabbage is limp and light brown, about 10 minutes.
Mix cabbage, beef and noodle mixture, 1 1/2 cups sour cream, caraway seed, paprika, salt and pepper.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Spread 1/2 cup sour cream on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Very good.
Enjoy!

title: fish loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and pack into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until firm (45 minutes).

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash two big bananas with fork and cover with about 1/4 cup orange juice.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Combine bananas and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Cook in oven at 425°.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: michael's sweet things
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4 pieces.
Dip them into the melted margarine.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and dip the buttered biscuit pieces into this mixture.
Place in a 9-inch cake pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Then spread topping over them.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Mix cake mix and next four ingredients.
Grease three cake pans and flour them.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: pound cake #4
directions: Cream
together margarine and shortening; add sugar and beat until well mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add	flour
and
beat well.	Batter will be very thick. Put into 10-inch greased tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Start in a cold oven.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with Fritos or crackers.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and lemon. Cook in a double boiler until custard thickens. Let cool. Add tbsp. of sugar to egg white and beat. Add to the cool mixture. Fold in whipped cream. Layer 3/4 of the crumbs mixture in a 1 1/2 qt. rectangular pyrex dish. Spread lemon mixture over crumb layer. Sprinkle the remaining crumbs over the lemon mixture. Put in freezer and chill. Cut and serve.

title: my home state maryland fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in flour, then in beaten egg, then in milk, then bread crumbs.
Coat well.
Brown well on both sides in Crisco or oleo, then add the poultry seasoning, salt, pepper, onion and water.
Simmer until well done.

title: creamy cheese dip
directions: Place cheese in bowl and mash with a fork.
Blend in mayonnaise and sour cream, creaming until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill several hours.
Makes 2 cups.
Very good with raw vegetables.

title: cherry blossom cheese tarts
directions: Beat cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla for 5 minutes.
Place cupcake liners in muffin tins.
Put one wafer in each.
Fill with mixture halfway.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: In first bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups flour, 3/4 cup sugar and sliced apples.
In a second bowl, mix 1/2 cup milk, 1/2 cup oil and 2 eggs.
Mix these together and stir into first bowl.
In 3rd bowl, mix 1/4 cup flour, 1/4 cup brown sugar, 2 tablespoons butter, 1/2 cup walnuts (chopped) and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Crumble over apple mixture.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sauerkraut beef balls
directions: Soak the caraway seed in water 5 minutes.
Combine ground beef, sauerkraut, oats, salt, pepper and caraway seed.
Mix well. Shape into 36 balls (about 1 1/2 of mix to each one).
Roll balls in flour; brown in hot oil, then cover and cook slowly for 25 minutes.

title: spicy slaw
directions: Bring to boil and pour over cabbage.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: bacon and cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Cut shortening into flour, baking powder and salt until crumbly. Stir in cheese and bacon. Add milk to make a ball of dough. Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface. Knead gently 10 times. Pat dough into a round about 1/2-inch thick. Cut biscuits and place on a greased cookie sheet about 1/2-inch apart. Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 12.

title: whole beef tenderloin
directions: Heat sauce first.
Sauce recipe can be doubled and served with meat as an "au jus".
Leave tenderloin whole and form as a log. Fold under thin end.
Tie with string about 4 to 5 times to hold shape.

title: diet cookie
directions: Boil apples, raisins, dates and water for 3 minutes. Add vegetable oil and cool. Add the other ingredients. Mix well and refrigerate overnight. Drop on cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Refrigerate in airtight container.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, cocoa and sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.
Drop by spoonfuls or make balls; roll in powdered sugar, then in granulated sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven very slowly. Will easily burn on bottom if oven is too hot.

title: old kentucky nog
directions: Combine sugar, milk, pudding, egg yolk and nutmeg until well blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff with sugar.
Fold into eggnog mixture.
Chill until very cold.

title: 9-day church slaw(low calorie)
directions: Bring mustard seed, vinegar, oil, sugar and salt to a boil. Let cool a minute or two, then pour over cabbage and onion mixture.
Refrigerate before serving. (Can be stored up to 9 days.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix 1 cup strawberries in blender or slice thinly.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water until smooth. Add blended berries.
Cook over medium heat until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Stir in remaining berries.
Pour in shell and chill for 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: pearl brode's pecan pralines
directions: Cook to hard ball stage.
Beat until slightly cloudy.
Add 2 cups pecans.
Drop on greased wax paper.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Combine cheese; spread seasoning and sour cream.
Mix well. Place broccoli in baking dish and top with chicken and cheese sauce.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili cheese dip(mexican)
directions: Brown hamburger meat, drain.
Put into crock-pot set on high. Add cheese, stirring until it melts.
Add other ingredients. Serve with Fritos or Doritos.

title: emma harvey's chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add cocoa.
Mix applesauce, oil and nuts.
Stir well.
Bake in 10 x 13-inch aluminum foil lined pan. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: grandma's crumb cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in shortening to make crumbs.
Reserve 2/3 cup crumbs for topping.
In remainder of crumbs, mix in cream of tartar, soda and milk.
Add beaten eggs. Mix well and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: seafood turnovers
directions: Boil or microwave vegetable package until ready to serve. Place cooked vegetables in a bowl (may be cut to smaller size) and add oysters and crabs (sardine size cans are recommended, canned chicken may be substituted).
Use rolling pin and flour to roll out biscuits to about 6 to 8-inch diameter.
Spoon in vegetable and seafood mixture into rolled biscuits (approximately 2 tablespoons per biscuit).
Fold biscuit into half circle turnover.
Seal edges with a fork.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush on beaten egg on outside of biscuit.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes or until outer shell browns.
Makes 8 turnovers.

title: nancy's chicken 'n stuffing
directions: Dredge chicken in flour seasoned with salt, pepper and garlic. Melt butter or margarine in frypan and saute chicken 6 minutes each side.
Spread prepared stuffing in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken atop stuffing.
Cover with Muenster cheese. Bake in a 325° to 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve with salad, vegetable and cranberry sauce.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all soups together in a baking dish and mix rice in with soups.
Place chicken on top of mixture.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Brush melted butter on chicken and cover with foil.
Bake in oven at 250° for 3 hours.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Add first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Cover top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon over cheese.

title: trio ball(cheese)
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy and well blended.
Add onion and sauce.
Shape into ball.
Cover with chopped pecans and chill until firm.
This mixture may be rolled in chopped parsley and served with toothpicks.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar with enough cream to make a runny drizzle over top.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and milk to a boil over medium heat until it reaches soft ball stage.
Stir in marshmallow cream, then stir in peanut butter. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased with butter. Cool and cut into squares.

title: vegetable pasta
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles.
Drain and set aside for a minute.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Wash and stem strawberries.
Add sugar and rum and refrigerate overnight.
One hour before serving, pour chilled champagne and chilled wine in punch bowl.
Add strawberry fruit mixture and stir lightly.
Float lemon and orange slices on top.
Garnish cups with lemon and orange slices.
Great for entertaining.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
I also add 1 cup of cooked small elbow macaroni.
It makes the salad go further and tastes just as good.

title: bread pudding
directions: * Best made with week-old bread.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Add egg.
Mix in spinach.
Stir well.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: pecan praline candy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and syrup in saucepan.
Cook until forms soft ball in cold water or 236° on candy thermometer.
Take off heat and drop in pecans.
Stir for 5 minutes.
Drop on wax paper teaspoonful at a time.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix together corn flakes and melted butter.
Put half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion over cabbage. Mix together soup, sour cream, milk, mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour over cabbage. Sprinkle remaining corn flake mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lip licking cheese dip
directions: Cook meat and onion together until brown.
Pour off fat.
Mix in all other ingredients and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes or until all cheese is well melted.
Stir all the time or will stick to bottom.
Serve while hot.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown chops in frying pan.
Make layers of chops and sliced onions in a casserole dish.
Pour mushroom soup over this.
Bake, covered, one hour at 350°.
Use your own judgment about potatoes and onions, just enough of each to make a layer over chops. Serves 8.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Cream well; add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add milk and flour.
Sift with salt and soda, measuring flour after sifting.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour well-beaten batter into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until done (toothpick comes out clean).
Cake keeps moist for several days.
Yield:
20 to 30 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Simmer chicken in water with salt, pepper and celery until tender.
Add potatoes, onion and carrot to boiling broth; cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in parsley.
Prepare Pot Pie.

title: steak fajitas
directions: Cut steak in 1/4 inch thick strips about 3 inches long.
Brown steak in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Drain fat.
Add onion, Fajita seasoning mix and 1/4 cup water.
Mix. Add bell peppers (thinly sliced) and onion (sliced).
Cook over medium heat until water is reduced and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Warm tortillas.
Place 1/2 cup of meat mixture into a tortilla, add salsa and sour cream to taste.

title: kid dough
directions: Stir all ingredients to combine.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat until thickened. Store in airtight container.
It will harden when left out.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form into balls.
Makes about 60.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chunky pimento cheese
directions: Let cream cheese and Cheddar cheese come to room temperature. Puree pimento in blender or processor.
Mix the three ingredients, then sprinkle garlic salt on top and mix into cheese mixture.

title: bow tie pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix together mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in bow ties, orange sections, apple and celery.
Cover; refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: Put pineapple, dry jello and sugar to a boil on low heat. Cool.
Beat cream cheese and baby food together.
Beat evaporated milk until foamy.
Mix all ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until set.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat.
Mix all ingredients.
Put 1/2 of mixture in hot skillet.
Sprinkle on 1/2 of cheese.
Add rest of mixture and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: ketchup
directions: Boil all ingredients except cornstarch and 1/4 cup vinegar for one hour.
Put through a food mill.
Return liquid to a boil Add cornstarch and 1/4 cup vinegar and whisk into juice.
Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add remaining ingredients. Beat until creamy.
Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned chicken pie
directions: Cook rice, celery, and peppers.
Cook chicken in water or in oven; save the stock.
Melt butter and add flour, mix until smooth.
Gradually blend in milk, stock, and half-and-half.
Cook and stir until sauce is creamy and slightly thickened, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased shallow baking pan, cover with biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in casserole pan.
Place sauerkraut over chicken; top with Swiss cheese.
Pour salad dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: onion-tomato soup
directions: Peel and slice onions thinly.
Saute in butter in large saucepan.
Add tomatoes, beef broth and spices.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Serve with toasted French bread.

title: quick spaghetti
directions: Lightly brown the ground beef.
Add to the cheese flavored spaghetti, the ground beef, catsup and barbecue sauce.
Put all ingredients in a large pan and simmer on a very low heat for several hours.
Makes a yummy spaghetti that kids especially like.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Brown meat with onions. Do not add salt. Peel and slice potatoes and place in large oven bowl. Judge according to your own family. You may use more. Now salt. Mix hamburger with sliced potatoes. Mix together the soups and pour over mixture of meat. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Mix and shape into crescents.
Bake in 325° oven about 20 to 25 minutes.
Don't overbrown.
Roll in sugar when cool.
Store in tight container.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger and onion and drain excess grease.
Add soups. Do not add any water; mix together.
Layer 1/2 Tater Tots on bottom of baking dish.
Pour hamburger mix on top.
Place remaining Tater Tots on the top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheddar cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Thin with a small amount of cream if necessary.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in toasted nuts or parsley.
Chill.
Great for holidays and parties.

title: pumpkin pie(madge's)
directions: Mix in order listed above, dry ingredients first.
Stir altogether until well mixed.
Pour
into
unbaked
pie
shell. Bake at 425° for 15
minutes,
then reduce temperature to 350° for 40 minutes.
Baking
time
will vary depending on temperature of filling and oven.
A
knife
inserted in middle of pie should come out clean when done.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked crust.
Cook 50 to 60 minutes (until it sets).

title: finger ham biscuits
directions: Cook first four ingredients in saucepan 10 to 15 minutes, stirring well; baste on little finger dinner rolls that have been sliced in half horizontally.
Layer thin sliced ham (or ground ham), then Mozzarella cheese, more ham and more Mozzarella cheese; as many layers as you want.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and drain spinach.
If too large, tear into pieces. Combine oil, sugar, vinegar, onion, salt and mustard.
Beat in blender until dressing becomes thick and syrupy.
Pour over spinach, bacon and eggs.
Let stand about 1/2 hour.
(For convenience, prepare dressing ahead and refrigerate.)

title: summer surprise dessert
directions: In shallow 9x12 glass dish, combine fruit and mix. Sprinkle brown sugar over fruit-top with sour cream. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 3-4 hours or overnight.
To serve, gently stir the fruit and spoon into sherbet glasses.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add 1/2 tablespoon chili powder and add tomato sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix hamburger mixture and cooked macaroni together in 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish.
Put shredded cheese on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mom's pork chops
directions: Roll meat in egg-milk mixture, then in crackers.
Place in iron skillet and fry medium-low heat until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: spicy lasagna
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and green chilies, sugar, salt and basil.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Line bottom of greased, shallow 2-quart casserole with 1/3 of the noodles.
Mix chives with sour cream and Ricotta cheese.
Spread 1/3 of the mixture over the noodles. Cover with meat sauce.
Repeat layers twice.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all vegetables. Combine other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Good with barbecue.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook peppers until tender.
Mix meat, eggs, onion, rice, tomato paste and 1/2 cup grated cheese together.
Stuff peppers and around peppers with mixture in baking dish.
Cover with 1 1/2 cups grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Remove chicken from bones and arrange pieces in lightly greased casserole.
Saute onions in 1 tablespoon oil until clear, but not browned.
Add carrots, celery and 1/2 cup chicken broth (stock from cooking chicken).
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add to casserole, then add the mushrooms (drained).
Dilute the cream of chicken soup with 1/2 can of broth.
Pour over meat and vegetables in casserole. Arrange biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until biscuits are done.

title: sweet potato medley
directions: Arrange potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place remaining ingredients, except nuts, in saucepan. Cook 2 to 4 minutes until sauce thickens. Remove from heat.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: steak rolls
directions: Cover each slice of steak with salt, pepper and mustard, then 1/2 slice of bacon and thin sliced raw onion.
Roll lengthwise and fasten with a wooden toothpick.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.
Turn at 25 minutes.

title: chicken cocktail salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Fold in chicken and chill 30 minutes.
Add fruit cocktail and almonds.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 5.

title: grannie brockman's icebox rolls
directions: Break yeast into mixing bowl; add water.
When dissolved, add sugar and milk.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add dry mixture to liquid.
Beat with a spoon until smooth.
Melt lard; add to dough mixture.
Mix well.
Add rest of flour to make a soft dough.
Put in refrigerator until ready to use.
Roll out as thin as pie crust.
Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place a dot of butter on one and put one on top of the other.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat and serve.

title: sarah's sugar cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar, eggs, flavoring and water.
Blend in flour and baking powder.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: savory meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of soup, beef, 1/2 can of onions, egg and Worcestershire sauce thoroughly.
Shape firmly into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.
Makes 2 pies.
Make and let set.
Keep in icebox.

title: mexican rice
directions: Add oil, celery, onion, green pepper, garlic and cumin to 12-inch skillet.
Saute over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until rice is browned.
Remove from heat.
Combine water and bouillon in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add to rice mixture; stir in tomato sauce.
Heat just until mixture simmers.
Cover and continue to simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, 10 minutes before serving.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic over medium heat until tender.
Add Worcestershire sauce, thyme, parsley, hot sauce, salt and bay leaves.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add just enough broth to keep mixture from burning and slightly moist.
If using smoked sausage or shrimp, add now.
Cover; cook until done.
If using cooked meat, add now.
Stir often.
Cook another 15 minutes, uncovered.
Add rice.
Turn heat to low.
Simmer until excess moisture is absorbed.
Do not overcook.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
On wax paper, sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in pumpkin.

title: barley soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Worcestershire sauce.
Boil gently for 2 hours.
Add Worcestershire sauce, and serve.
Makes 7 to 8 servings.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add eggs, sugar, shortening and flour.
Mix well and refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in uncovered casserole dish at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cornish hens
directions: Combine preserves, orange juice and butter to make glaze.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar
together; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternating with coffee.
Stir in apples and nuts. Bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Prepare Jiffy cake mix according to box directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan, baking for 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese, slowly adding 2 cups milk.
Add instant pudding.
Spread mixture over cooled cake.
Drain can of crushed pineapple and spread over pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
If desired, cover with chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: stroganoff of beef
directions: Brown meat cubes in butter.
Add onions and mushrooms and cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste, sliced olives, salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Stir into meat mixture; cover and simmer 1 hour. Mix cornstarch and water; stir into mixture.
Add sherry.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Just before serving, add sour cream. Serve with cooked noodles or browned potato balls.

title: almond cookies
directions: Mix together and form into balls; press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: potato carrot casserole
directions: Mix together potatoes, carrots and onion and put into greased pan.
Blend milk with chicken or celery soup, salt, pepper and melted oleo.
Pour over potato mixture.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese on top.
Bake for another 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: rhode island potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into baking dish.
Don't cover. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Potatoes will get very brown like home fries.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Mix rest of ingredients and add all dry ingredients at once.
Mix a few seconds.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: new-fashioned fettuccine alfredo
directions: In large skillet melt margarine over medium heat; stir in 3/4 cup light cream (or half and half), stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add fettuccine to skillet.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup light cream (or half and half), cheese, pepper, nutmeg and salt.
Cook 1 minute.
If desired, serve with additional cheese and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mary's caramels
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, cream and salt in a heavy saucepan. Place over low heat.
stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to 232°, stirring occasionally.
Add butter and evaporated milk alternately.
Stir occasionally to prevent scorching.
Continue cooking to 242° to 243°, firm ball stage.
Stir under thermometer test in cold water, firm ball stage.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and stir to blend.
Pour into an oiled 8-inch cake pan. Do not scrape pan.
Don't make candy on a rainy day, it won't set.

title: scones
directions: Mix dry ingredients and butter into "nuggets."
Combine eggs and milk; mix until blended.
Rinse raisins in hot water to plump them.
Add to dough.
Knead briefly.
Put dough on floured board. Sprinkle flour on top.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 3-inch rounds.
Place close together on greased baking sheet. Brush with beaten egg.
Bake 12 to 13 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Roll into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans and parsley flakes.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Saute diced onion, diced carrots and diced celery until tender.
Stir in flour and cornstarch.
Cook until bubbly.
Gradually add chicken stock (room temperature) and milk (room temperature).
Blend into smooth sauce.
Add baking soda and cheese (cut into pieces).
Stir until thickened; season with salt and pepper.
Add parsley and cayenne pepper.
Garnish with paprika.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Empty first 4 ingredients into bowl.
Fold in sour cream. Chill.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Place paper muffin cups in muffin tins and fill each 3/4 full.
Place muffin tins in freezer and freeze. Serves approximately 12.

title: nell's breakaway bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
In large bowl, pour boiling water over Crisco; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, eggs, flour and yeast; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Let stand at room temperature 2 hours.
Roll and cut out.
Butter. Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pans.

title: southwestern egg puff
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with additional picante sauce and sour cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli and drain.
Arrange in a greased baking dish.
Place the chicken on top.
Mix the soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder together.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
This dish can be fixed the day before and kept in refrigerator.
Allow a little extra heating time in this case.

title: peanut butter tarts
directions: Slice cookie dough in 9 even pieces, then quarter each slice. Place each piece in mini tart pans. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove pan from oven immediately and push a Reese's cup into each cookie. Refrigerate until shine leaves chocolate. Remove from refrigerator and gently lift out with tip of knife.

title: brown sugar chewies
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
They will appear soft but will set up as they cool.
Cut into squares.
Add flour, flavoring and nuts to first 3 ingredients.
Mix and bake as instructed.

title: all-day beef stew
directions: Place ingredients in Dutch oven in order given.
Cover; bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Heavenly on a cold winter day.

title: turkey joes
directions: Cook turkey and onion in skillet, stirring and separating turkey, until it's no longer pink.
Stir in sauce and relish.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Serve on buns.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Put in pan with graham cracker crust. Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: bacon tater tots
directions: Wrap strips of bacon (cut in half, if you like) around frozen Tater Tots.
Place on baking sheet with bacon ends down on pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: banana cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add egg, bananas, vanilla, oats and walnuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast 1 hour or so, drain and save broth.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.

title: peach cream cheese pie
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Drain peaches (saving juice).
Beat with mixer 2 minutes, pudding, salt, baking powder, flour, butter, egg and milk.
Pour into pie plate.
Place peaches over batter. Cream 2 minutes, cream cheese, peach juice and sugar.
Spoon onto other mixture.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over top of pie. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients and softened butter, mixing until blended.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Makes one loaf. Bread may be frozen.

title: fried rice
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces; brown in large skillet.
Set bacon aside.
Pour rice into same pan (leaving the oil from bacon).
Crack 2 eggs over rice mixture; stir until eggs cook in. Add peas and corn; fry for 5 minutes on medium heat, stirring constantly.

title: glorified hash
directions: Place cover on roaster	and
bake
for	1 hour.
Do not open oven door for anything until the next morning!!!

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 25 to 30 minutes.

title: blueberry bread pudding
directions: Arrange half of bread cubes in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle evenly with cream cheese and 1 cup blueberries; top with remaining bread cubes. Whisk together eggs, 4 cups milk, sugar, butter and maple syrup; pour over bread mixture, pressing bread cubes to absorb egg mixture. Cover and chill 8 hours. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 30 minutes or until lightly brown and set. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Stir together remaining 2 cups blueberries and blueberry preserves in a saucepan over low heat until warm. Serve blueberry mixture over bread pudding.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: hot mushroom canapes
directions: You must use melba toast with this recipe.
Regular crackers will become soggy.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend well and refrigerate overnight.
Especially good with raw vegetables.

title: squirrel hash
directions: Mix squirrel, potatoes, broth and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dust with paprika.
Cook in skillet with the melted butter for about 30 minutes over low heat, stirring often.

title: mississippi chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together, adding chocolate chips last. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a Bundt pan.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a bowl slowly.
Boil 1 minute; cool.
Place on sheet cake while cake is still warm.
Put holes in cake with straw.

title: drunken chicken
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, combine first 5 ingredients. Add chicken pieces and turn to coat.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight, turning chicken occasionally.
Spray grill rack with nonstick cooking spray.
Place 5-inches from coals.
Place chicken, bone side down, on rack and grill 20 minutes, brushing with marinade. Turn chicken.
Brush with
marinade and cook 10 to 15 minutes until cooked through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, bananas and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in loaf pan.

title: hot cheese toast
directions: Cook bacon and drain.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl, except bread and bacon.
Crumble bacon and add to mixture, then set aside.
Cut crusts from bread slices on all sides.
Spread each slice generously with cheese mixture.
Cut each slice into 3 strips.
Place on baking sheet; cover and refrigerate 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to directions on package.
Fill paper cupcake liners 2/3 full.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cut sausage into quarters.
Brown sausage.
Drain grease in skillet with butter.
Brown bell pepper and onion (cut up small). Drain juice from Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add enough water with juice to make 3 cups.
Add all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add seasoning to taste before boiling, then add rice.
Bring to boil again.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let sit for 5 minutes.

title: honey buns
directions: Place rolls close together in pan.
Combine other ingredients and spoon over rolls.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread potatoes in greased casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add soup and sour cream; mix well and spread on top of potatoes.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pinch bread
directions: Thaw loaf and let rise until double its size.
Mix together melted butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Pinch off golf ball size dough. Roll in mixture.
Place in ungreased loaf pan. Continue until dough is gone. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Flip onto serving plate. Enjoy.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
(You can use food processor to grate carrots and apple.)
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
In a separate bowl, beat the eggs, vanilla and oil. Stir into flour mixture just until combined.
Spoon into well-greased muffin cups, filling almost to top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon pork chops and sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oil in 12-inch skillet or Dutch oven over medium-high heat until hot.
Add pork chops; cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until browned.
Remove pork chops from skillet.
Add 1/2 cup of the pineapple liquid, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon to skillet; blend well.
Reserve remaining pineapple liquid.
Add sweet potatoes to skillet; turn to coat with liquid.
Add pork chops. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 15 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in bell pepper and pineapple chunks.
Cover; simmer an additional 5 minutes. Transfer pork chops to warm platter.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan, except lemon slices. Cover and simmer 20 minutes; remove spices with slotted spoon. Serve hot with lemon slices.
Serves 6.

title: barley bake
directions: Melt butter and brown onion and barley.
Mix with other ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, stirring occasionally.

title: onion bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Stir down and put into 2 well-greased bread pans or 1-pound coffee cans. (Dough will be bubbly.)
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nan's roasted potatoes
directions: In a large roasting pan, pour some oil and add potatoes, onions and spices, a little at a time; stir often to coat with spices.
Top with cheese.
Add water around the edges.
Cover pan with foil.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.
When potatoes are cooked, take foil off and brown under the broiler.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Mix together the ketchup and brown sugar. Wrap chestnuts with bacon and hold together with toothpicks.
Bake 1/2 hour to 45 minutes on broiler pan (so grease will drip down) until bacon is done. Dab on paper towel to rid of excess grease.
Place in baking dish.
Spoon ketchup mixture over all (trying not to get all over toothpick).
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out rolls onto a cookie sheet.
Use both cans.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes and cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing and spread over cooled dough.
Cut up raw vegetables into small pieces and spread over mayonnasie mixture.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: new orleans take-out jambalaya
directions: In large skillet, heat the oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion; saut for 8 minutes or until the onion is lightly browned.

title: macaroni and bean bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray a 9-inch square glass baking dish with a cooking spray.
Combine macaroni, 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese, beans, tomatoes and peppers; mix well.
Spoon into prepared dish.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Grease bottom only of square 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour, oats, baking powder and salt.
Spread evenly in baking dish.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Microwave on High (uncovered) for 4 minutes; turn dish a quarter turn.
Microwave until no longer doughy, 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool; cut into about 2-inch squares.

title: low calorie rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Pour into 1-quart casserole. Cover with plastic wrap directly on surface of hot pudding.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Remove plastic wrap.
Sprinkle with more cinnamon, if desired.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, cream margarine with granulated and brown sugars until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa and baking soda. Gradually add to margarine mixture, beating until well blended. Stir in chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break bacon into small pieces.
Mix all together in large serving bowl.

title: do ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes, mash or whip until smooth.
Add the rest of ingredients except butter.
Put in a greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through.
I find this recipe great for Thanksgiving or Christmas.
Can be made ahead a couple of days or frozen.

title: whipped jello
directions: Bring Jell-O, pudding and water to boil.
Stir occasionally. Let cool. Add Cool Whip. Add strawberries. Mix well. Cool.

title: fat free sour cream banana bread
directions: Beat together sugar and applesauce.
Add eggs, bananas, sour cream and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; stir until moistened.
Pour into sprayed (or greased and floured) pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Use toothpick test.
Store in refrigerator.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease a bowl.
Crumble in
biscuits, pour hot water over and mash thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Start baking in
oven at 350°.
Turn down temperature and cook about 30 minutes.
Don't cook too hard. (Mixture will shake in the pan.)

title: flan(extremely easy)
directions: Put a large pot/pan with water in the oven and turn the temperature to 325°.

title: tuna dip
directions: Use tuna fish or dried beef.
Mix all of the above by hand. Shape into ball or mold of your choice.
This is good with crackers.

title: maple salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and maple syrup.
Add dates, pineapple, coconut, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix together and chill.

title: little mushroom spinach imperial
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions, omit salt until later depending
on
how
well the bread crumbs are seasoned. Drain
well.
Combine all other ingredients and transfer to a buttered
casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly. Serves 8.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Place potatoes in a microwave-safe dish.
Sprinkle with melted butter and chopped parsley, chives or sage.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes, rearranging potatoes after 5 minutes.
Let rest for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Microwave for another 4 to 6 minutes on High until cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: salmon balls
directions: Mash potatoes and add to all the other ingredients.
Roll into 2-inch balls, then roll into corn meal until coated.
Fry in small amount of oil, turning often until all sides are browned.
Top with favorite white sauce or melted cheese and serve.

title: black forest cake
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, water and cocoa. Bring to a boil. Boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat and blend in butter. Cool overnight. Place the chocolate mixture in bowl of electric mixer. Add eggs and vanilla. Sift together remaining ingredients. Gradually add to mixing bowl. Grease and flour a 9-inch spring-form pan. Pour batter into pan. Bake in 350° oven for 70 minutes or until done. Cool thoroughly. Remove from pan. Slice irregular top away and dry to provide crumbs for decoration. Slice cake in 3 equal layers. Place bottom layer on cake plate. Brush top lightly with kirsch (wild cherry liqueur).

title: rocky road cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
In small bowl mix walnuts, raisins, marshmallows and semi-sweet chocolate.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and blend on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Seed peppers and chop coarsely.
Place 1/2 pepper and 3/4 cup vinegar in food processor on high until smooth.
Repeat with rest of peppers and vinegar.
Combine pureed peppers, red pepper, sugar and salt in large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Add pectin.
Cook, stirring often, for 30 minutes or until mixture sheets from a metal spoon.
Quickly pour into sterilized jars with 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover at once with 1/8-inch paraffin.
Cover with metal lids.

title: easy chicken soup
directions: Saute vegetables in butter or margarine.
Add flour.
Stir well to blend.
Add broth and chicken tenders.
Cook for 45 to 60 minutes, or until tender.
You can add a handful of cooked noodles or rice.
Freezes well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Add oil; beat well.
Add strained carrots and mix well.
Add flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Beat 4 minutes.
Add pineapple, walnuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured loaf cake pan and bake at 375° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, broccoli, onion and bacon in a bowl.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour the sauce over the vegetables and mix to coat.
Let it set overnight in the refrigerator to mix flavors.

title: pimiento cheese pinwheels
directions: Mix well the pimientos that have been mashed, the pimiento juice, the cheese (crumbled fine), relish, mashed hard-boiled eggs, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Cut crust from bread slices. Flatten each piece with hand or roller.
Spread each slice with filling and place 4 stuffed olives in the center across the width. Roll each slice in waxed paper.
Place in tight container and freeze.
When to be used, take rolls out and slice into bite-size slices with electric knife.
Let dry out on paper towels before serving.

title: mama's cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch square dish at 350°.

title: clam chowder
directions: Set aside 1 cup clam liquid.
Boil potatoes until tender. Drain potatoes in a bowl and save 1/2 cup of the liquid.
Fry onion; don't burn.
Stir in clam liquid, 1/2 cup potato liquid and clams.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 10 minutes.

title: chicken parisiane
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Salt and pepper.
Place, skin side up, in baking dish.
Blend wine and soups together well.
Add mushrooms, if desired.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove cover and bake for 10 more minutes. Place chicken on rice and mix chicken drippings with sour cream and heat on low until hot.
Spoon over chicken and rice and pour in gravy boat on the side.

title: pineapple banana split dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and melted butter or margarine.
Press mixture firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate to chill slightly.

title: kentucky chocolate pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 30 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Makes 8 servings.

title: amish hat
directions: Spread peanut butter on each cracker.
If you are using large marshmallows, cut each one in half with scissors and put 1/2 on each cracker.
If using small, place 3 on each cracker.
Place in microwave or under broiler and cook until marshmallow is soft.

title: chicken pizza muffins
directions: Preheat broiler.
Arrange muffin halves on rack in broiler pan.
Spread each muffin with 1 tablespoon spaghetti sauce. Divide chicken and cheese evenly on muffins; sprinkle with red peppers.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 3 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Brown flour in oil; add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring until smooth.
Add water, cook until thick.
If raw tomatoes are used, cook longer to be sure tomatoes are done.
Add more sugar if too tart.
Serve with hot biscuits, sausage or bacon.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix well,
roll
into small balls.
Put on cookie sheet, mash with fork.
Cook at 250° until light brown.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, butter flavor, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into three 9-inch round greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Use as a basting sauce when grilling chicken, pork or beef.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put everything in casserole dish and put
a lid on.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: golden puffs
directions: Sift flour.
Add salt and baking powder.
Blend in water and egg.
Drop in hot fat by tablespoonfuls and fry until golden brown.
Dust lightly with confectioners sugar.
Serves 6.

title: scripture cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter until light.
Blend in molasses. Stir together flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and honey. Mix eggs and buttermilk.
Add liquid mixture and dry mixture alternately to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins, figs and almonds.
Turn mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Loosely cover with foil and bake for 50 minutes more.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Brush all sides with wine or orange juice.
Warp in foil and store 1 to 2 days in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter crunchies
directions: Boil sugar and corn syrup.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies or corn flakes.
Mix well.
Spread on a greased cookie sheet.
Let harden.
Cut into 2 or 3-inch squares.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix as directed; spread in large pizza pan and bake 15 minutes or until done; cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar. Spread over crust.
Layer fruit, beginning with bananas.

title: beef stew
directions: Using crock-pot, mix broth, water and soup; mix.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
To thicken broth, make paste of equal amounts of water and flour (1/2 cup each).
Add to stew, stirring until well blended.
Add Veg-All and cook 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake in a loaf pan or coffee can for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mucho macho meat sauce
directions: Remove casing from sausages.
In a hot skillet, brown sausages.
Add ground beef, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until browned.
Add sauce, pepper flakes and red wine.
Reduce heat to simmer, cover and cook for about 30 minutes.
Check occasionally for consistency.
Serve over favorite pasta, topped with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: fabulous fish in a boat
directions: One piece of foil per serving.	Lay fresh fish on foil and shape into "boat".	Add 2-3 Tbsp. chutney on top of fish. Sprinkle with curry powder to taste.
Layer with fresh veggies. Sprinkle with
salt and pepper and about 2 Tbsp. chicken broth.
Dot with butter, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or place on hot grill for 20-25 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Remove pulp from zucchini and cut into small chunks.
Boil for 10 minutes in small amount of salted water.
Drain well and mash. Brown meat; add mushrooms, onion and green pepper.
Cook a bit longer.
Add zucchini, soup and croutons.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake uncovered for 1/2 hour in 375° oven.

title: aunt thelma's pound cake
directions: Beat butter, Crisco, sugar, lemon and vanilla until creamy. Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and milk (add flour half at a time until mixed well).
Beat all ingredients until creamy.
Pour in large greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pone(virgin islands native recipe)
directions: Mash sweet potatoes while hot.
Add sugar and whole eggs.
Mix well.
Mix in butter with fork.
Add milk; blend well.
Add lemon rind, juice and dry wine.
Add salt, baking powder and cinnamon sifted together.
Add raisins and almonds.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken joseph
directions: Mix together and let sit in refrigerator for 2 hours (marinate).
Grill and serve.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar together.
Pat in an 8 or 9-inch pan to form a crust.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
Take out and chop stems.
Add chopped stems to Parmesan, garlic, parsley, salt, pepper and oregano. Fill mushrooms; place these in a baking pan.
Now mix olive oil and melted butter and pour this over stuffed mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all together and put in baking dish.

title: chicken andouille gumbo
directions: Cut chicken into eight pieces; cover with water and simmer approximately 1 hour, until chicken is tender and easily removed from the bones.
Pour off stock and set aside.
Allow chicken to cool; debone and set aside.
Meanwhile, slice okra and saute in about 2 tablespoons of oil until all ropiness is gone (about 1/2 hour).

title: somemore bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Stir in corn syrup, margarine and vanilla until smooth.
Pour over cereal.
Mix thoroughly.
Add marshmallows.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.
Cut into bars.

title: sunken cherry cake bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together, except for pie filling.
Put cherries one after another, leaving about 1/2-inch space in between on top of batter.
(They will sink while baking.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tested is done.

title: charolais beef in sour cream
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sear the steaks in the butter on both sides in 2 large skillets on top of the stove.
Place steaks in large casserole; place in oven to keep hot while you pour cream in pan in which you have seared the steaks.
Stir in sherry; pour over the steaks.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and dried beef dish
directions: Mix and let stand
overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, bake in 325°
oven for 1 hour.

title: carrot-rice bake
directions: In a saucepan, bring water, bouillon granules and salt to boiling. Stir in carrots, rice, butter and thyme. Return to boiling. Turn mixture into 2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 325° for 25 minutes. Stir. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer. Garnish with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: fish cakes(fiskekaker)
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor and mix on low speed until mixture becomes a smooth paste.
Shape into balls and fry over medium heat until golden brown and cooked through.
Serve with red potatoes and creamed cabbage.

title: if you like cabbage
directions: Cook bacon slightly in
medium
size
pot.
Saute onion and garlic.
Crush tomatoes in small bowl.
Add to pot and add 1 1/2 cans water, sugar,
salt and pepper.
Ten minutes before turning off, add cabbage,
potatoes and black-eyed peas.
Cook cabbage until tender, but
not
mush.
Try
green
lima
beans instead of black-eyed peas.
Serve
with corn bread and butter (pepper sauce if you like).

title: chocolate ice cream sauce
directions: Mix milk, sugar and chocolate together and cook in a double boiler 20-25 minutes. Beat 2-3 minutes and add vanilla. This is good either warm or cold.

title: caramel pie
directions: Slowly melt 1/2 cup of sugar in heavy saucepan or skillet over low heat until it begins to caramelize.
Meanwhile, mix remaining sugar, cornmeal, flour, egg yolks, milk, margarine and vanilla in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
When pie mixture comes to rolling boil, add the caramelized mixture. Continue stirring and cook until thick.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 400° until crust is brown.
Beat egg whites with
3 tablespoons sugar.
Top pie with meringue and brown.

title: old-fashioned no crust apple pie
directions: Beat egg, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased and lightly floured 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chip dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Cut up green chilies and add along with rest of ingredients.
Serve with corn chips or nacho chips.

title: pot roast
directions: Place frozen chuck roast in roaster.
Put the mushroom soup over roast. Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or longer, if desired.
Uncover and place in veggies.
Re-cover and continue to bake approximately 1 hour or until veggies are tender. Serve in pan.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Beat up cottage cheese, Cool Whip and orange jello, then blend in oranges and pineapple.
Ready to eat.

title: steak au poivre
directions: Season the steaks with the salt. Spread a tablespoon of the mustard on one side of each steak. Coarsely grind the peppercorns in a coffee grinder or with a mortar and pestle or in a food processor. With your fingers, press 2 tablespoons of the pepper into each steak. Turn the steaks over and repeat the process with the remaining mustard and pepper.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix together egg, cornstarch, flour, chicken broth and salt. Add pork cubes and stir until each piece is well coated.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Pour 3 cups oil into wok or large skillet and set over high heat.
When hot, drop in pork cubes, one by one.
Fry for 5 to 6 minutes regulating heat so that pork turns a crisp golden brown without burning.
When done, remove pork with a slotted spoon into a small baking dish and keep warm in oven.
Fry remaining pork; add to first batch.
Pour sauce over the pork and serve at once.
Serves 2 to 4 as main dish or 4 to 6 with Chinese meal.
