title: sausage and noodle casserole
directions: Brown sausage and add onions, salt, pepper and oregano.
Add soup, milk and Cheez Whiz; pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine; add coconut and chopped pecans.
Brown on top of stove in a pan and set aside.
Combine cream cheese and milk with mixer and fold in whipped topping.
Put 1/2 of mixture in each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/2 jar of caramel sauce on each pie. Sprinkle with 1/2 of browned coconut mixture.
Repeat layers and freeze well.
Serve right from freezer.

title: hospitality pineapple meatballs
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 1/2 cup juice.
Place pineapple tidbits on paper towels to drain.
Soak bread in small amount of water; squeeze out.
Mix bread, beef, eggs and onion salt.
Shape into small balls, enclosing pineapple tidbit in each ball.
Brown slowly in butter and oil, shaking pan to keep balls round and evenly browning.
Drain excess fat.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Store in airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Pour melted oleo on top.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 40 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: This recipe is for a bread machine. Use fresh milk cycle. Note: Welbilt ABM 100, Dak & Mister loaf use sweet bread cycle.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: In medium bowl, place flour, salt, sugar and Crisco.
Put seal on bowl and shake briskly.
Add water; replace seal and shake again.
Dough will need very little handling.
Roll out on floured pastry cloth; enough for a two crust pie.

title: italian twist salad(makes 6 servings)
directions: In bowl, combine macaroni, salami, cheese, carrots and celery.

title: creole flounder
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Place fish on greased baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients. Spoon over fish. Bake 5 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Garnish with pepper rings.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Mix sour cream and soup.
Place 2 slices of beef on each breast, roll, wrap with partially cooked bacon strips and secure with toothpicks.
Pour sour cream and soup mixture over chicken which has been placed in casserole dish.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Leftovers freeze well and warm nicely in microwave.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Prepare and bake cookie crust.
Meanwhile, in large bowl, beat eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended. Stir in pecans.
Immediately pour over hot crust; spread evenly. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until filling is firm around edges and slightly firm in center.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: curry dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate one hour.
Serve with vegetable tray.

title: hickory sauce
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate.
Makes just over 1 gallon.

title: gayle's yeast rolls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let stand until yeast is dissolved and is foamy, about 15 minutes.
Add powdered milk, oil and enough self-rising flour to make a stiff dough. Grease 9 inch cake pans with melted butter.
Pour dough out onto a floured board and knead lightly.
Roll out and cut with a biscuit cutter, placed in greased pans.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Very easy and good.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: glazed fresh apple cookies
directions: Mix well and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Frost with butter frosting.

title: mocha squares
directions: Take loaf angel food cake; rub off brown crust on cake.
Slice lengthwise in thirds, then in squares.
Chop peanuts in processor. Mix together sugar, oleo, coffee and vanilla.
Roll squares in sugar mixture, then in peanuts.

title: sausage bread casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
In a bowl mix cooked sausage, eggs and cheese.
Spray a 10x13 pan with pam...place 1 can crescent rolls, flat into bottom of pan.
Pour mixture on rolls... Place remaining rolls on top.
Cook according to directions on crescent roll pkg.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in 1 1/2 or 2-quart microwave dish. Cook on High 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and oleo; stir.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Add soda and stir fast until it turns white.
Pour out on greased baking sheet as thin as possible.
Do this quickly.
Let it cool.
Break into pieces.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: After processing cheese well, add eggs.
Blend again for a short time.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and cream.
Cover blender and process again.
If a thin crust is desired, add Bisquick and blend.
Pour mixture into a pie pan and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool, then refrigerate.

title: marie's hot pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well.
Add eggs beating well after each.
Add flour alternately with juice.
Beat well, add vanilla. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in tube pan at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix box of pudding with juice of crushed pineapple.
Fold in pineapple, Cool Whip, lemon juice, marshmallows and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Spread oil over crackers.
Stir well.
Sprinkle salad mix, garlic powder and dill weed over crackers.
Mix well.
Do not bake!

title: chicken cacciatora(pollo alla cacciatora)
directions: Wash and clean
chicken;
pat dry.
Cut chicken into 20 pieces, cutting breast into 2 pieces.
Heat oil in deep frying pan or Dutch oven.
Saute
chicken and bay leaves in oil until well browned,
approximately
minutes.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add
mushrooms,
garlic
and
onion
to drippings. Saute over medium
heat
until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook
for 35 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve with rice or
a side of spaghetti.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp and onion in butter for 5 minutes or until shrimp are tender.
Add mushrooms and cook for 2 to 3 minutes more. Sprinkle in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream and cook gently for 10 minutes, being careful not to boil mixture.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Put salmon in large bowl; remove bones. Stir in already mixed up egg. Then pour in flour and roll into balls; put them in hot frying oil in deep fryer. Remove when brown.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs and beat well. Beat in peanut butter, vanilla, baking soda and salt. Stir in oatmeal. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Butter 2 qt. casserole.
Put eggs into food processor and cover.
Process at stir until beaten.
Add remaining ingredients.
Push mix button and process only until corn is thoroughly into batter.
Pour into casserole and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes until firm.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump in order of pineapple, cherry pie filling and cake mix into an ungreased pan. Do not mix!
Slice up margarine over top. Sprinkle with chopped walnuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipping cream.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Beat egg and sugar until light; add vanilla extract and shortening, melted with chocolate.
Blend well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk; add nut meats.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350° 10 to 12 minutes).
While warm, frost with Mocha Chocolate Frosting.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients thoroughly with hands. Roll into tiny balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in skillet.
Remove bacon to drain on paper towel.
Stir-fry onion in pan with bacon drippings for 2 minutes.
Add rice and stir-fry 7 minutes.
Add soy sauce, water and crumbled bacon.
On low heat, pour egg on top of rice mixture. Stir-fry for 3 minutes or until eggs are cooked.
Makes 4 servings.

title: justine sugar cookie(cutout, rolled)
directions: Mix dry and liquids separately.
Mix all, adding liquid and dry (should resemble pie dough).
Chill 1 hour.
Refrigerate. Roll onto heavily, floured board.
Cut with cutter.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Toast bread lightly and cut each piece into strips.
Place into rectangular baking dish (approximately 12 x 8-inches).
Pour butter over each toast layer.
Repeat.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove all skin from the chicken, rinse and dry thoroughly.
Season, coat each piece with oil or dip in milk.
Shake to remove excess and roll in crumbs.
Let stand briefly so coating will adhere.
Place chicken in oiled pan (line pan with foil for easy clean-up).
Do not crowd; pieces should not touch.
Bake 45 minutes or more.
Crumbs will form a crisp "skin". Treat for picnics.
Yield:
4 servings, approximately 270 calories per serving.

title: roast duck(hungarian style)
directions: Sprinkle duck with salt, pepper and garlic, inside and out. Tie legs together.
Prick skin all other with fork.
Put duck side up in shallow roasting pan (do not add water), basting with juice from duck.
Cook duck for 1 1/2 hours or until tender in a 350° oven.
Strain juices; save 1/4 cup.
Cook white ice and mix with 1/4 cup juice.
Cut up duck and arrange on heated platter with rice.

title: val's ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in loaf pan and bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Melt margarine; saut onion and celery.
Mix with stuffing. Place stuffing mixture in 13 x 9 pan, reserving 1/2 cup.
Top with shredded chicken.
Mix soups and broth and pour over chicken.
Top with reserved stuffing mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl; beat until well combined. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool; remove.

title: claude's mostaccioli
directions: You will need two stock pots; a 12 quart. and an 8 qt., a large skillet and a large strainer.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in pot and cook until thick. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: salsa dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl and chill the dip for 30 minutes or longer.
Serve with tortilla chips or vegetables.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Dump pineapple and cherry filling into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Empty dry cake mix evenly over the pineapple and cherry filling.
Put pats of butter or margarine over the top of the dry cake mix.
Bake at 350 for 35 minutes.
Nuts can be added after pie filling for a nice touch.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, salt, pepper, garlic salt and onion.
Then add all other ingredients.
Simmer until done.

title: low-fat french fried potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and slice into thin wedges.
Mix ingredients and add half of mixture to potatoes.
Place in oblong flat baking dish. Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Baste occasionally with remaining liquid.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: ginger cookies(mother's recipe)
directions: Measure flour, sugar, salt and ginger into a large mixing bowl.
Add Crisco and molasses.
Mix together 1 minute.
Stir soda into sour milk; mix thoroughly.
Add to rest of ingredients.
Add eggs.
Beat 3 to 4 minutes on medium speed of electric mixer. Drop by large teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350° (depends on oven).
Yields 6 dozen medium cookies.

title: potato salad vinaigrette
directions: Boil potatoes carefully so as not to split or crumble them. Cool slightly and cut into quarters.
Do not peel.
Pour wine over potatoes and toss gently.
Mix vinegar, oil, herbs and spices. Pour over potatoes and season.
Serve with still warm or chill. Makes 6 cups.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables, celery and onion according to package directions.
Drain.
Add mayonnaise and cheese to veggies and mix. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over the top.
Drizzle melted butter over the top of the cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 30 minutes, until crackers are browned.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all and spread on cake.

title: yellow applesauce bundt cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
In mixing bowl, combine cake mix, applesauce and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes on high speed.
Pour 2/3 batter in pan.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on batter.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool upright at least 25 minutes.
Remove from Bundt pan.

title: dilled okra pickles
directions: Pack scrubbed okra in pint jars (do not cut off stems).
On top of the okra, lay several fresh celery leaves, one piece of garlic, a slice of pepper and the dill (do for each jar).
Mix brine and bring to boil.
Pour over okra; seal immediately.
Let stand at least 3 weeks.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients; pour in a greased pie pan.
Bake in
oven	for 1 1/2 hours.
Test the center until the knife blade comes out clean.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, onion, egg and bread crumbs together. Put tomato sauce and water into skillet.
Put in meat balls and cook on low heat until done, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: flaky butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vegetable oil, slightly beaten egg and vanilla.
Add corn flakes,
oatmeal, nuts and coconut.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and add rest of ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet and bake for 12 minutes at 350°. Freeze well.

title: fit for a king(cranberry side dish)
directions: Whip first 3 ingredients together.
Then add cranberry sauce, pineapple and whipped topping; mix well.
Put in mold or pretty dish. Refrigerate overnight.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix together, heat and eat!

title: cinnamony fried apples
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, melt butter.
Add apples, brown sugar and lemon juice.
Toss lightly.
In small saucepan, heat cinnamon candies and water until melted.
Pour over apples. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until apples are tender (about 5 minutes).

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Stir all the ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Pour into your graham cracker crust.
Chill for at least 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Blend all remaining ingredients together.
You may use a pastry blender or by hand.
Spread on top of apples and press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are done when tested with a fork.
Great served with vanilla ice cream.

title: date nut rolls
directions: Cream together sugar, dates
and
margarine
and boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add	Rice
Krispies, pecans and vanilla, if desired.
Stir	well
and dip out by teaspoonfuls. Roll in Angel Flake coconut.
Makes about 3 dozen rolls.

title: black cake
directions: Put everything in a bowl and stir for 4 minutes.
Put mixture in a pan and put in a 7° oven for 8 minutes.
When the oven rings, the cake is done.
Take the cake out of the oven and eat it.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in long baking dish.
Mix rest into melted butter. Drop fruit into mixture.
Swirl in.
Bake until light brown. Bake at 350°.

title: pasta bean soup
directions: Saute pepper, onion and basil in oil.
Cook pasta al dente (not soft).
Heat water.
Add all ingredients.
Simmer and stir occasionally.

title: sausage and eggs
directions: Cook sausage in a large skillet over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble; drain well.
Place sausage in a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Set aside.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until foamy.
Remove crust from bread; cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Stir bread cubes and cheese into egg mixture.
Pour egg mixture over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Yield 6 servings.

title: chicken in wine sauce(microwave)
directions: Combine onion and butter in an 8-inch square dish. Cook on High 4 to 5 minutes, until onion is tender. Add chicken.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes longer.

Stir once. Add salt, pepper, wine and pepper. Cover with plastic wrap. Cook on High 4 minutes. Add mushrooms. Blend cornstarch with broth. Stir until smooth. Stir into dish. Cook on High 4 to 5 minutes or until sauce is thickened. Stir twice.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out excess water.
Melt margarine and mix with all ingredients.
Form balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: italian sausages and peppers
directions: Cut sausages into bite size pieces and brown in large skillet. Slice onions and peppers and add to drained sausages.
Add garlic salt, parsley and tomatoes.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir until well blended.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Let cool, then break into pieces.

title: r e o speedwagon
directions: *Use 5 when using vanilla ice cream or 4 when using cookies and cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift the flour, salt and sugar together.
Cut in the Crisco. Add egg, vinegar and water, mix well together.
Divide into 5 equal parts.
This dough freezes well.
Make dough into ball and flatten to about 1 inch thick before freezing.
Defrost at room temperature when ready to use.
Makes five 9-inch pie crusts.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and Post Toasties.
Pour that on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: poinsettia punch
directions: Tie cinnamon and nutmeg in cheesecloth bag and put in saucepan with 2 cups of water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in gelatin and sugar and allow to cool.
Remove bag and add remaining ingredients just before serving.
Pour over ice.

title: charlotte
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1/4 cup cold water and let soften for 5 minutes.
Mix sugar, 3/4 cup water, lemon juice and mandarin juice together in a pan, add gelatin and heat, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Chill until just barely thick, beat until frothy.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry, and fold into gelatin mixture.
Whip the cream to soft peaks and fold in.
Line a 2-quart mold with drained mandarin sections, spoon in the Charlotte and chill. Unmold before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tuna corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; spoon into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: canning pork in brine
directions: Pour 1 cup brine in a quart jar. Fill with pieces of raw pork. Do not pack too solid.
Remove air bubbles.
Cold pack 1 hour. When serving meat, roll pieces in flour and fry.
Discard the brine.
This recipe will make brine for 14 to 15 quarts.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In a large bowl, beat 1 1/4 cups sugar, shortening and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, then bananas.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Beat until sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Chill 30 minutes. Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on cookie sheets.

title: orange no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Form into small balls. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook vegetables; drain and wash with cold water after cooking. Add celery, mango, red beans and onions.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in fat.
Add water and cover; simmer 1 hour. Combine in different pan cornstarch, salt, brown sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce.
Cook until slightly thick, stirring constantly.
Pour sauce over hot pork, let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Add green pepper, onion and pineapple chunks.
Cook 2 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: orange icing for cake
directions: Melt butter and combine all other ingredients together. Spread on cake.
Will cover 3 layers.

title: baked beans with meat
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour in oven at 350°. Cook low for 4 hours in crock-pot.

title: chicken bombay
directions: Split, bone and quarter breasts.
Shake in bag with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in a little oil.
Take chicken out and set aside in casserole.
Add remaining ingredients to drippings.
Cook and blend for 1 minute.
Cool and pour over chicken.
This may be refrigerated or bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: marcelle's mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Saute pepper and onion.
Mix with chili powder, soups and tomatoes.
Layer chicken mixture and Doritos in a baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and cocoa.
Stir well.
Add eggs. Add milk and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mozzarella and basil salad
directions: Core, seed and chop tomatoes. Slice Mozzarella or dice into bite size pieces. Place in bowl. Mix basil, olive oil, lemon juice and salt and pepper. Pour over tomato mixture and marinate at room temperature at least 2 hours.

title: giant oat-peanut cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and oats.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars until blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture by hand; mix until well combined.
Shape into 2-inch balls.
Place 6 balls on ungreased baking sheet; flatten each to 3-inch diameter.
Bake in 350° oven 15 to 17 minutes, until golden.
Cool on rack.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 24 large cookies.

title: coconut date skillet rolls
directions: Combine sugar, dates and eggs in a skillet.
Cook over medium heat about 10 minutes until mixture pulls away from sides of pan. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and nuts.
Carefully stir in cereal.
Cool slightly.
Moisten hands in cold water and shape mixture into small balls.
Roll in Angel Flake coconut.
Chill and store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Take 1/2 of the berries and mash.
Add food coloring to suit, then add cornstarch and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and cool thoroughly.
Add remaining berries, which have been sliced.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with Cool Whip or Dream Whip.

title: country chicken
directions: Cut chicken tenders into two inch pieces. Spray large pan with Pam or use 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil. Cook onions and peppers over medium heat about 10 minutes. Add meat and mushroom soup, cook 10 to 15 minutes or until warm. Serve over rice. Other meats may be used.

title: vanilla refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to cream mixture. Mix well.
Shape mixture into rolls, 1 1/2-inch in diameter, on Saran Wrap.
Wrap and seal ends.
Chill several hours or overnight.	Slice thin and bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes three to four dozen cookies.

title: chocolate chip caramel rolls
directions: Combine brown sugar, 2 tablespoons butter and corn syrup. Cook on 100% power for 1 to 2 minutes or until butter is melted and brown sugar is dissolved.
Stir to combine.
Evenly divide mixture among six 6 ounce custard cups.
Set aside.

title: four bean bake
directions: Simmer bacon, onion, vinegar, brown sugar, etc.
Pour over beans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake additional 15 minutes more.

title: bar cheese spread
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put in containers and cool.
Can be refrigerated for a month or more.

title: mackerel cakes
directions: In large bowl mix drained can of mackerel, eggs, onion and flour.
Hand mix; well.
Preheat frying pan.
Add oil.
Using a large spoon, place mixture into frying pan and press lightly.
Cook on both sides until golden brown.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in Pyrex dish.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
Pour over melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Add 2 1/2 cups peeled peaches over top of batter.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Cut margarine into cake mix until crumbly.
Pat mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, building up slightly around the edge. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Arrange pie filling on warm crust. Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on apples.
Blend sour cream and egg.
Drizzle over apples.
(Topping should not completely cover apples.)
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are brown.
Serve warm.

title: salad
directions: Combine and chill for several hours.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute rice in olive oil until golden brown.
Separately mix together all remaining ingredients.
Pour into sauteed rice and bring to a boil.
Reduce to low heat and simmer approximately 20 minutes.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

title: gravy and biscuit(the army calls this sos)
directions: Melt butter in 1-quart saucepan.
Mix in flour to make a paste.
Add milk slowly, blend with wire whisk.
Add beef, garlic salt, parsley flakes minced onions, pepper and chives.
Heat until slightly thick (gravy thickness).
Serve over biscuits or toast slices or English muffins.

title: white frosting for cakes
directions: Combine water, corn syrup, sugar and cream of tartar of salt in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat about 3 or 4 minutes or until you can hold your spoon up and it makes a string.
Beat egg white in bowl until stiff.
Pour syrup mixture slowly into egg whites while beating.
Add vanilla.
Beat until you think it is thick enough to spread on cake.
Very good.

title: tender buttery corn
directions: Mix corn, butter, salt, pepper and nutmeg in 1-quart casserole. Cover tightly and microwave until tender on High 3 minutes.
Stir. Cover and microwave 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare first 5 ingredients in salad bowl.
Brown hamburger. Pour in mild taco sauce and tomato juice.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
May use 1/4 of the grated cheese to sprinkle on hamburger mixture.
Pour over salad and toss.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine and let stand overnight.
Hollow out center of round loaf of bread (dark pumpernickel or spinach cheese flavor).
Cube bread section removed from loaf.
Fill hollowed out section with dip.
Serve with bread cubes to be used of dipping or spread on a mild cracker.

title: fancy cheese meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, seasonings and 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce.
Mix in ground beef.
On wax paper, pat the meat out into a 9 x 13-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle cheese over meat, leaving a small margin around the edges.
Using wax paper as guide, roll up meat, sealing in cheese completely, and remove wax paper.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except 7-Up.
Freeze and store until day needed.
Thaw to slush stage (about 4 hours).
Pour into punch bowl and add 7-Up and serve.
Serves 30 to 35.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (8-inch) round cake pans.
By hand, combine cake mix, eggs and oil.
Carefully fold in orange sections and juice.
Spoon batter into cake pans.
Bake 15 minutes, or until done.
Remove cake from pans and cool completely before frosting.
This cake must be kept refrigerated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease flat casserole.
Put cubed cheese in bottom.
Steam broccoli until tender-crisp; drain.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter over top of cheese in dish with broccoli.
Mix melted stick of butter with crushed Ritz.
Sprinkle over broccoli to cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: old time chocolate gravy
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour; mix well.
Add water and cook over medium heat until desired thickness.
Add vanilla.

title: vivian's wonderful punch
directions: Make jello according to directions on package. Stir, then add sugar. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add almond extract and all fruit juices. Stir. Add water.
Stir.
Freeze for at least 24 hours. Add ginger ale to taste (about three 2 liter bottles).

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight jar or other container.
Use 1 to 3 teaspoons per cup of boiling water according to taste.

title: raspberry sheet
directions: Mix as pie crust.
Roll half out on cookie sheet.
Roll the rest in strips.
Spoon 1 can raspberry pie filling (about 2 cups) onto crust.
(If using frozen raspberries, add sugar until sweet enough.
Spoon some juice out and add about 4 tablespoons cornstarch or use about 4 1/2 tablespoons tapioca in place of cornstarch and mix.
Put in the cold sweetened raspberries.
Cook raspberries until thickened.
Cool.)
Place remaining strips of pastry on top of raspberry filling and seal edges.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit in flour after cutting. Cream butter and sugar. Sift flour and spices. Add eggs and flour alternately with milk. Stir in fruit and nuts. Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Space so cookies will not run together. Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool and store in closed container.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well, then apply the rest and put it in an electric or hand ice cream maker.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs in small bowl, then alternate eggs and flour into creamed sugar and butter.

title: hot and spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Stir well.
Use as a marinade on steaks, chops or chicken, then brush remainder on while grilling.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Chop cranberries, oranges and apples in food processor.
Add the sugar; mix well and cool in the refrigerator.
Can be frozen.

title: caliente chile salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine chili and salsa; simmer 15 minutes. Crumble chips into serving dish.
Spoon hot chili mix over chips. Top with lettuce and cheese.
Add more salsa, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Mix all ingredients well. Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. (Freezes well.)

title: barbara bush's cookie recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt onto waxed paper.
Beat butter, brown sugar, white sugar and egg in large bowl with electric mixer until fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in hot water and vanilla.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until blended and smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: ida's chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour.
Add baking powder, soda and salt.
Sift again and set aside.
In a large bowl, cream butter.
Gradually add sugar and brown sugar, creaming well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in the sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal, coconut and chopped nuts. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Store cool cookies in tightly covered container.

title: deer meat delight
directions: Place meat in an iron skillet with 1/4 cup oil.
Brown meat. Add peppers, onions, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until pepper, onions and garlic are transparent looking.
Add mushroom soup and milk.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Put on hot rice and enjoy!
This is good with hot corn bread.

title: fairy pie
directions: Cream the butter and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Add milk and 1/2 cup of
flour, then baking powder, mixed with the 2 tablespoons of flour.
Turn into two 9-inch cake pans (greased).

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Break crackers into divided pieces and arrange on a cookie sheet.
Melt two sticks butter or margarine in a saucepan; add 1/2 cup sugar and bring to a boil.
Boil one minute.
Pour warm sauce over crackers on cookie sheet; place in moderate oven and bake for five minutes or until golden brown.

title: grandma's fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, cut up bananas.
Add pineapple, walnuts, sugar and marshmallows.
Whip cream and add to fruit mixture.
Stir ingredients until well mixed.
Keep refrigerated until served.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Add limeade and lemon juice and pour into shell.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream oil, oleo and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs. Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in and blend well.
Chill for 1 hour. Roll a teaspoon of dough into a ball.
Roll ball in granulated sugar.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: manhattan norwegian pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg.
Add baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Pour into well greased pan (8-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "broccoli ham ring"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Coarsely chop ham, broccoli and onion. Grate cheese. Mix all ingredients except crescent rolls and set aside. Arrange crescent triangles in a circle on a 13-inch baking stone with bases overlapping in center and points to the outside. There should be a 3-inch diameter circle in center. Evenly spoon filling over base. Fold points of triangle over filling and tuck under base at center. Filling will not be completely covered. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and rinse.
In a large casserole or crock-pot, mix all ingredients together.
Stir in ground beef. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Crock-pot: low setting for 3 to 4 hours.
Good for party.

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking powder.
Cream butter and gelatin, beating well.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture, blending well.
Roll out cookie dough and cut out shapes or force dough through a cookie press onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° about 8 minutes or until edges fare golden brown.
Yields 60 cookies.
Serving size is 3 cookies.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Melt shortening in a skillet, add onion, cooking until transparent.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain fat.
Pour beef/onion mixture into a 2 quart casserole dish.
Mix in gravy. Add carrots and peas in alternate layers.
Then cover mixture with mashed potatoes.
Place several slices of margarine on top of potatoes and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 25-30 minutes.
Before serving top with shredded cheese and melt.

title: onion celeste
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower in separate pans until tender. Drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, cauliflower, 2 cups of cheese and the onion; separate and place into two 10-inch greased and floured cake pans.
(We use the new coated pans; they are very nice to cook with!)

title: cream cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Make your balls and put some nuts inside of it, then roll it in nuts.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar, eggs one at a time, vanilla lemon extract.
Then fold in flour by hand.
Add Cointreau.

title: cheerwine ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: corn slaw
directions: Combine corn, onion, green pepper and carrots.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Combine vegetables and dressing together.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix fruits, nuts and cheese together in a salad bowl.
Combine sauce ingredients in a small saucepan and cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over apple salad mixture while hot.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Dip eggplant in eggs and then cover with bread crumbs.
Fry your eggplant in vegetable oil and put on side.
Thinly slice Mozzarella cheese. Now you're ready to assemble your dish.
Using a large casserole, layer your eggplant, then cover with tomato sauce, Mozzarella and sprinkle your grated Parmesan cheese.
Continue this layering until you're finished.
Place your casserole dish, uncovered, in oven set at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove; cool for 30 minutes and then ready to serve.

title: cheese-broccoli strata
directions: With a donut cutter or a glass, cut 12 circles from bread.
Fit leftover bread scraps into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Place cheese in layer over bread.
Add a layer of broccoli. Arrange circles of bread on top.
Combine eggs, milk, onion, salt and mustard.
Pour over other ingredients in pan.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 55 minutes.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Cut Kielbasa in sliced bite size.
Put in large frypan on medium high heat.
Brown lightly, mix all other ingredients.
Pour over Kielbasa.
Cook on simmer about 20 minutes or until thickened. Serve with rice.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour and milk.
Begin and end with flour.
Add flavoring and coconut.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: jewish brownies
directions: Beat well and spread on warm cake.
Cool and cut brownies. Sooo good.

title: herbed baked fish
directions: Place fillets in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Blend milk and flour in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir constantly until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute longer. Add salt, garlic salt, pepper, thyme, oregano, green onion and dill weed.
Pour sauce over fish.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: festive chicken salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine reserved syrup and cream cheese, mixing well.
Add pineapple and then add combined remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Cut avocados in half.
Hit seed with sharp edge of knife and pull out seed.
Spoon out avocados into small mixing bowl.
Mash or beat the avocados.
Add other ingredients and beat together. Garnish with lettuce and tomatoes.
Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.
Recipe may be doubled, tripled, etc.

title: haystacks
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, cream, molasses and salt.
Bring to a soft boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat and add coconut and butter.
Mix well.
Pour onto a buttered platter and cool.
When cool enough to handle, form into haystacks.
Place on a buttered platter.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: gumboe
directions: you have to cut the oyeins.

title: spinach and swiss quiche
directions: Beat the first 2 ingredients until creamy; add balance of ingredients and beat until well mixed. Pour into prepared pastry shell and bake at 375° for 25 to 45 minutes.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and well beaten egg.
Add flavoring. Add flour to the mixture a little at a time, alternating with the milk until all are in.
Roll to 1/8-inch thick, cut into cakes and bake in moderate oven until lightly browned.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Bake yellow cake in 2 round pans according to directions on box.
Whip cream, sugar and egg yolk until fluffy.
Add chocolate. In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add to chocolate mixture with vanilla.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for about an hour, until top is golden brown.

title: liver and onions
directions: Rinse liver and place on waxed paper.
Squeeze lemon juice on both sides of each piece of liver.
Sprinkle both sides of liver with salt and pepper.
Dredge liver in a mixture of flour and salt and pepper placed in a brown paper sack.
Quickly brown both sides of liver in a frypan of hot Crisco.
Remove liver from frypan and place on a plate or other container.
Set aside.
Slice onions and gently saute until translucent and a golden color.
In very large saucepan or Dutch oven pan, place a layer of liver.
Sprinkle with flour and a layer of onions.
Repeat until all liver and onions have been placed in pan.
Add 2 or 3 cups of water and place pan over medium heat.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add more flour and water. Cook another 30 minutes.
Liver should be tender and in a nice thick brown gravy.

title: tuna lunch
directions: Toast bread and remove crusts.
Place 6 slices on rectangular baking pan.
Spread tuna mixture on each.
Top each with slice of cheese. Cover with 2nd slice of toast.
Now cover each sandwich with broccoli mixture.
Cook uncovered 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: oven omelette
directions: Fry bacon until brown; drain. Saute onions, mushrooms and green pepper. Beat eggs with milk and salt. Stir in bacon, onion, mushrooms, green pepper, 2 cups Monterey Jack and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese. Pour in greased 2-quart baking dish. Can be covered at this point and refrigerated overnight, if desired. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until set and lightly browned. When almost done, sprinkle with remaining cheese. If you choose to refrigerate, allow extra time for baking.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Season pork chops and brown in oil.
Place onion slices over meat.
Mix soup and Worcestershire and pour over all.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add water occasionally if needed.
The soup becomes a delicious brown gravy.

title: joann's barbecue sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and puree.
If you wish, you may marinate the meat in this sauce.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Lightly brown ground meat; drain.
Add chopped onion, bell pepper, celery and eggplant.
Cook until vegetables are tender, adding water as necessary to keep from sticking.
Mixture should be moist but not too watery.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add rice just before serving.

title: shrimp with tomatoes
directions: Thaw shrimp; pat dry with paper towels.
In a 10-inch skillet heat olive oil or cooking oil over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp, garlic, oregano and basil; cook about 3 minutes or until shrimp turn pink, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes and lemon juice; cook and stir 30 seconds or until heated through.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley; serve over rice, if desired.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan (flour pan).
Mix eggs, sugar, Ricotta cheese and vanilla until nice and creamy.
Pour over cake batter.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown.
Check center with knife.
Bake a few minutes longer if knife is wet.
Cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Melt margarine and add flour and milk; salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until thickened.
Pour sauce in casserole dish. Spread out.
Add peas.
Heat mushroom soup.
Spread on peas. Sprinkle on cheese.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, onions, cheese, chestnuts and mayonnaise well. Pour vegetable mixture into a greased casserole dish.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers and pour melted margarine over crackers. Bake for about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger, drain any grease.
Add garlic powder, crushed red pepper, sliced olives, chopped onion, mushrooms, spaghetti sauce, sugar, and chopped bell pepper.
Cook 1 pkg. noodles.
Drain noodles, and cover with sauce.

title: mom's ginger cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar, molasses and egg in bowl.
Sift flour, soda and spices together and add to molasses mixture.
Stir until well mixed. Roll small amounts into balls between the palms of your hands.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. The cookies will be crispy around the edges but slightly chewy in the middle.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients and cracklings.
Add milk and eggs.
Put into a hot skillet (iron) which has been prepared with oil and a dusting of cornmeal to keep from sticking.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 30 minutes to brown correctly.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix beaten egg with flour, salt and pepper.
Dip meat in batter and fry until golden.
Combine everything else except cornstarch in another pan.
Heat through, then add cornstarch. Cook until gravy is clear.
Remove from heat; add meat and heat thoroughly.
Serve with rice.

title: french silk mint pie
directions: Beat sugar with butter in a large bowl until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add melted chocolate. Stir in extracts.
Pour into crumb crust.
Refrigerate until firm. Garnish with mint leaves and maraschino cherries.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix egg, sugar and sour milk.
Mix well.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Sift dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Beat thoroughly.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour. (Sweet milk may be used instead of sour milk.
If sweet milk is used, omit the baking soda and increase the baking powder to 6 teaspoons.)

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt bark and chips in double boiler.
Mix in peanuts.
Drop on wax paper and put in refrigerator until set.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Mix sour cream, dry mustard, black pepper, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend for 2 minutes.
Add mayonnaise; blend for 2 minutes on medium.
Add Bleu cheese.
Blend on low for 3 minutes.
Must sit 24 hours.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie shells as directed; let cool.
In large bowl, combine the instant pudding, Dream Whip, milk and vanilla.
Mix with hand mixer.
Add instant coffee; mix.
Add Cool Whip, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into pie shells.
Top with grated chocolate and refrigerate.

title: deer jerky
directions: Combine ingredients for marinating deer.
Stir well to dissolve.
Marinate deer overnight.
Lay meat on oven rack; be sure to put aluminum foil down to catch drippings.
Cook 6 to 8 hours at 150° (the longer it bakes the crispier it is).

title: stuffed fillet of flounder
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil bottom of pan.
Take 4 pieces of fillet of flounder and place in baking dish.
Add a pinch of salt, pepper, oregano and parsley to each fillet.
Slice 2 pats of butter per fillet and put on top.
Divide crab meat into quarters; place on top of each fillet.
Top each fillet with one of the remaining fillets.
Add a little oil to the top of the fillets. Baste frequently while baking.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: salmon pasta salad
directions: Drain salmon; reserve 2 tablespoons salmon liquid.
Flake salmon with fork.
Combine reserved salmon liquid, olive oil, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper in small bowl.
Blend well.
Pour over pasta.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water (salted) for 4 minutes.
Drain. Mix with soup, mayonnaise, eggs, cheese, onion, salt, pepper and Accent.
Turn into a buttered shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with crushed cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: pickled okra
directions: Bring to a rolling boil; bring vinegar mixture to a boil. Pour into jars.
Makes 6 pints.

title: muffins
directions: Mix sugar and egg; add grapenuts, pineapple, bananas, bisquick and salt.
Stir till blended but not smooth.
Fill muffin tins almost full.
Bake at 425 degrees for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: lemon dropper
directions: Fill cocktail shaker with ice.
Pour fresh or prepared lemonade almost to top.
Add 2 - 3 shots of wicked cold lemon flavored vodka and shake.
Serve in chilled martini glass with slice of lemon and/or kiwi.

title: ginger dip with fruit
directions: Beat cream cheese, yogurt, honey and ginger root until creamy. Fold in pineapple.
Cover and refrigerate to blend flavors, 1 hour.

title: jam cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture and blend to soft firm dough.

title: liver with onions
directions: Season liver with salt and pepper.
Preheat skillet over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add butter and melt.
Saute onions until tender.
Add liver and brown about 2 minutes per side.
Add mushrooms with liquid to liver and onions.
Simmer, covered, over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and Worcestershire sauce. Gently stir and heat until hot, about 4 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Cream butter, shortening, vanilla and sugar (adding small amounts of sugar at a time).
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out dry.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apple slices in a baking dish.
Mix oats and brown sugar together in a bowl.
Spread evenly over apples.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Best when served hot, especially with ice cream.

title: cherry cheesecake pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese in a bowl until fluffy. Add sugar and sour cream. Beat 3 more minutes. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie crust. Spoon cherries on top. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix corn meal, salt and soda with creamed corn, eggs and milk.
Put cast-iron skillet in a 350° oven with 2 tablespoons oil and 2 tablespoons corn meal sprinkled on surface.
Heat until corn meal turns a golden brown.
Mix chopped onion and jalapeno with corn bread mixture.
Pour 1/2 corn bread mixture into hot skillet.
Spread ground beef over corn bread, then Cheddar cheese on top of meat.
Cover with remaining corn bread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let set for 15 minutes before cutting.
Enjoy!

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil 2 fryers in salted water until tender.
Brown 1 pound ground beef.
Grind meat together in a meat grinder along with 2 or 3 large onions.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Swirl through batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake(or rum cake)
directions: Cream sugar together with margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, nuts and coconut; fold in vanilla wafer crumbs.
Grease pan.
Cook for 1 hour at 300°.
Let cool at least for 1 hour.
Pour on 1/3 to 1/4 cup of rum, bourbon or brandy.
Leave for 3 days or longer, wrapped in aluminum foil.

title: plain 'ol potato salad
directions: Simply peel, dice and boil potatoes until tender.
Boil your eggs for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain water from potatoes while your eggs are cooling.
Peel eggs; dice and add to potatoes.
Use seasoned salt to taste, a dash of regular salt, 3 to 4 dashes of pepper and 2 to 2 1/2 tablespoons of mayo; stir.
Mix in 5 to 6 dashes of paprika.

title: mostaccioli primavera salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
During last 2 minutes of cooking, add asparagus to cooking water.
Drain pasta and asparagus.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly.

title: divinity
directions: Bring sugar, karo, and water to a boil, until a soft ball forms in cold water, and slightly thread spins from the spoon. Pour 1/3
of mixture slowly into beaten egg whites.
Beating constantly.
Continue beating for a few seconds, returning syrup to a low flame.
Add syrup to egg whites at intervals making 4 beatings, return syrup to low heat each time.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Continue beating until mixture holds its shape, when dropped from a spoon.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Swirl each piece to a peak.

title: old fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Add the molasses, oleo, water and sugar.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.
Roll in walnut size balls; dip in some sugar.
Place on cookie sheets that have been oiled.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until light brown.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger with onions, chopped green pepper and seasoning.
Drain.
Put into greased pie pan.
Combine eggs, Bisquick and milk.
Beat.
Pour over hamburger.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven.
Put sliced tomatoes and either grated or processed cheese on top.
Bake 10 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chow chow
directions: Mix onions, peppers, cabbage, green tomatoes, hot peppers and salt.
Let set overnight.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: First:
You get up at 9:00 am before mommy and daddy, but you have to be real quiet or they will hear you.

You go to the kitchen to fix you something and open the fridge to get something to drink cause you're real thirsty and you pull the pitcher of Kool-Aid out and make sure you drop it in the floor, then you go get a little chair and stand up on the counter to find something to eat and all there is is Rice Krispies or crackers or something so you just pull it down in the floor and get a knife and start cutting; by that time, mommy hears you and comes and gets you so you run really fast.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender and chill.

title: pot pie
directions: Mix together.
Roll and cut in squares.
Cook in stew.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Precook chicken in 4 cups of water with 1 spoon of salt for 20 minutes or until the meat is tender.
Mix vinegar, soy sauce, garlic and pepper balls.
Add on meat and bring to boil on medium fire for 15 minutes.
Occasionally stir and make sure liquid won't dry up.
In case, add additional water.
When the natural juice of the meat comes out, add potatoes, red pepper and laurel.
Cook on low fire for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 spoon of sugar before serving.

title: pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Dough will be a little tacky.
Cook with pizzelle iron. Use approximately 1 teaspoon batter for each pizzelle.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients and liquid ingredients separately.
Add liquid to dry mix, blend well.
Bake for 15
minutes at 350° in greased muffin tins.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk together and spread evenly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or 8-inch oblong pan.
Place layer of peaches on batter.
Melt oleo and pour over peaches. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peach melba crisp
directions: In a medium bowl, tear toast into coarse crumbs. Toss with butter, then set aside.
Peel and slice peaches. Sprinkle with sugar, ginger and lemon juice.
Let stand 1 minute.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes until peaches are soft and mixture is bubbly. Add berries and stir to coat.
Sprinkle toast mixture over all. Cook, uncovered, on High 3 to 5 minutes until mixture is again bubbly. Let stand 5 minutes or more. Serve, if desired, with vanilla ice cream.

title: fudgy saucepan brownies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in medium saucepan over low heat; stir in cocoa, blending until smooth.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Add sugar, vanilla, salt and eggs; beat until thoroughly combined.
Add flour and baking powder; mix well.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Spread batter into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until top is dry and tester inserted in center is almost clean.
Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: broccoli chicken tortellini
directions: In a large pot, boil noodles and tortellini for 5 minutes. Add broccoli and boil 3 more minutes or until noodles are tender. In a skillet, melt butter, then add cream and cheese while stirring. Drain large pot, then add chicken and sauce. Serve family-style with breadsticks.

title: baked ziti with pesto
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Oil an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. In large pot of boiling, salted water, cook pasta for 7 minutes. It will be partially cooked. Drain and rinse with cold water.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Boil 3 cups sugar and 3 cups water until it is a syrup.
Cool and mix with orange juice and fruit.
Freeze.
Can cut sugar to 1 1/2 cups and 1 1/2 cups of water.

title: cinnamon sweet potatoes(microwave)
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter, brown sugar and eggs.
Mash until smooth.
Pour into microwave-safe dish.
Cook on High for 5 to 6 minutes.
Top with marshmallows.
Cook another 2 to 3 minutes or until melted.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: fluff rice pudding
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and let cook until rice is soft, or until water is all cooked out.
Bring 2 cups milk to a boil.
Add the eggs, 2 cups sugar and 2 tablespoons flour to make a paste.
Add a little milk.
Add all of this to the rice, and cook until thick.
Keep stirring until done.
When finished, add 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Let cool.
Whip 1 can of Carnation milk and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add to the rice.

title: davis junction church chili("feeds a crowd")
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer at least one-half hour.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Put sugar, cream cheese and marshmallows into hot water and Jell-O mixture.
Add whipped cream, pineapple and nuts.

title: microwave spicy pecans
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a deep 3-quart casserole, mixing well.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes; stir well.
Then microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until the mixture reaches the soft ball stage.
Add pecan halves and stir until well coated.
Spread pecans on waxed paper and separate with a fork.
Cool completely.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Heat pineapple, sugar, egg, flour and vinegar until it boils and thickens.
Chill until cold.
Add chopped nuts and Cool Whip. Fold in diced apples.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter and cook for 9 minutes. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Cream together and pour into buttered pan. VERY GOOD!!!

title: pavlova
directions: Pavlova is named after the Russian ballerina.
It is the perfect finishing touch to your dinner party.
Light and airy.

title: poppy seed tea loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except poppy seed, and beat for 5 minutes.
Add poppy seed.
Pour into two floured and greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is dry.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in lightly-greased skillet.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp cheese mold
directions: Grease ring mold with Wesson oil; soak gelatin in 1/4 cup shrimp liquid.
Heat soup to boiling.
Soften cream cheese.
Add hot soup slowly.
Blend well.
Add gelatin.
Cool.
Add mayonnaise, celery and onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Wait until mixture thickens a bit, then pour into ring mold. Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours.
Turn out on platter.
Decorate with fresh parsley and serve with party rye bread.

title: cauliflower with corn flakes
directions: Cook cauliflower until just tender or from 6 to 8 minutes. Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients in a small skillet and brown slightly for 5 minutes.
Drain cauliflower and arrange on a serving plate, then sprinkle with the hot crumb mixture.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Cut meat, pepper and onion in small pieces.
Heat pan; melt Crisco.
Add meat and brown on medium heat, then put other ingredients and finish cooking, stirring continuously.
Can add vegetables if desired.

title: chocolate cream cushions
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, beat butter and sugar until creamy; beat in egg and vanilla.
In another bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, salt, and cocoa; add to butter mixture alternately with milk, beating just until smooth.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets, spacing cookies about 2 inches apart.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes or until firm when lightly touched.
Transfer to racks and let cool completely.
Meanwhile, prepare your choice of buttercream. Spread bottoms of half the cooled cookies with buttercream; top with remaining cookies, top side up.
Store airtight.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: saucy mushroom chicken(an easy no fuss way to make delicious saucy chicken.)
directions: Combine all ingredients in crockpot.
Cover; cook on LOW for 8-10 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: In a bowl, combine Seven Seas dressing, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add pasta and other ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.

title: apricot-glazed pears
directions: Use an 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place pears, cut side down.
Pour mixture of preserves (or jam) and juice over. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with ground nutmeg.
Great warm or cold.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple (with juice), jello and sugar until jello is dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Cream the cheese; add Gerber and blend.
When pineapple mixture is cool, add to cheese mixture. After completely blended, fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into mold and chill or pour into oblong 10 x 6-inch pan.
Serves 12.
tags: Gerber junior food apricot with tapioca

title: coconut sour cream layer cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
When completely cool, split both layers; combine sugar, sour cream and coconut, blending well. Chill.
Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture.
Spread remainder between layers of cake (split side).
Combine reserved sour cream mixture with Cool Whip until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together, beat in eggs.
Mix in cocoa, flour and milk.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 325° oven for 40 minutes, until cake tests done.
Turn oven off and remove cake from oven, sprinkle marshmallows over cake.
Return to oven for 5 minutes until marshmallows melt.
Spread frosting over hot cake.

title: oven baked beef stew
directions: In a bag, combine flour, salt, pepper and add beef cubes, 1/4 at a time.
Shake to coat.
Place beef in a 3 quart casserole and add carrots and onions.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef, onions and add garlic salt, oregano and salt to the ground beef.
Cook noodles, then mix ground beef, noodles and all ingredients (except cheese).
Pour in an ungreased and uncovered casserole dish.
Sprinkle the Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk together.
Pour into crust, then layer bananas and pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip, cherries and pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cut
cauliflower
and
broccoli
into bite-size pieces. Combine all vegetables into large bowl.
In separate bowl, mix mayonnaise,
oil,
sugar, salt and peppers.
Pour over vegetables and
mix
well.
Refrigerate overnight, stirring several times. Garnish
with crumbled bacon before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: yesterday's cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Place leftover cake cubes in the dish; set aside.
In a bowl, combine egg yolks and sugar.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Add flour and baking powder.
Pour milk and butter into mixture; stir well.
Add vanilla extract.
Pour batter over cake; bake for 30 minutes. Heat broiler.

title: pecan or english walnut pie
directions: Mix well and pour in pie crust and bake at 300° or 350° until done.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer all ingredients.
Just before serving, toss with Catalina dressing.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Set aside.
Cream oleo, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water.
Add eggs and dry ingredients.
Slowly fold in chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix Ranch dressing, yogurt, cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Place roll dough on cookie sheet in a rectangle (2 cookie sheets).
Press seams together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread dressing on crust.
Top with vegetables and Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix ingredients together and drop from spoon into hot oil. Turn, then drain on paper towel.

title: debbie's soup
directions: In heavy large pot, cook meat in small amount of oil; season with salt and pepper.
When meat is done, add canned veggies; don't drain.
Add remaining ingredients, stir, cover and cook on low boil (simmer) for 1/2 hour until pasta or rice is done. Serves 6.

title: nut fingers
directions: Beat butter or margarine in large bowl with electric mixer at high speed until fluffy.
Add the 3/4 cup of 10x sugar, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in nuts.
Shape dough into 3-inch logs. Place, 1-inch apart, on cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 25 minutes or until pale golden brown.
Roll in 10x sugar while still hot.
Cool on wire racks.
Roll cooled cookies again in sugar to coat evenly.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Sift the baking soda with the flour.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a tube pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 350°
for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Stir in corn syrup, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with foil. Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cover and chill.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure flour, granulated sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa in a bowl.
Blend in milk and Butter Buds.
Stir in Grape-Nuts.
Pour into a square pan, sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Stir together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: In a 4-quart ice cream maker, combine condensed milk, Butterfingers and vanilla; stir. Add whole milk to fill line. Stir. Freeze as directed.

title: tea time tassies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Form shells by rolling into balls and pressing with thumb into small muffins.

title: crock-pot dip
directions: Cut cheese into small squares.
Add to crock-pot with salsa. Turn crock on low temperature.
Brown sausage first and drain; add to pot and mix well.
Brown hamburger; drain and add to pot.
Keep crock on low temperature.
Eat with tortilla chips.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Peel carrots; slice in 1/4-inch pieces.
Put in saucepan and barely cover with water; cook 10 minutes or until tender-crisp. Drain.
Cut bell peppers and onion into chunks (bite size).
Mix together soup, sugar, oil and vinegar in pan.
Bring to a boil. Pour over vegetables.
Let marinate 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: shortcakes
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix all ingredients, adding milk to make moist like pie dough.
Do not make too moist.
Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 23 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm or cool with milk or cream and fresh berries.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix with hand in dishpan.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Generously butter a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut bread into 1-inch slices.
Arrange bread in single layer over bottom of pan.
Beat eggs, milk, sugar, salt and vanilla in a large bowl until mixed well.
Pour over bread. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together well.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in tube pan.

title: sharp cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add all ingredients (except paprika). Mix very well.
Chill until firm, then shape into a ball.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: banana chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, mix oleo, egg and banana.
Add dry ingredients and chocolate chips.
Stir just until moist.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° until done.
Kids love these!

title: betsy's pasta salad
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package instructions.
Rinse in cool water.
Add broccoli florets, cherry tomatoes and black olives to spaghetti.
Pour Italian dressing over pasta and vegetables.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for at least 2 hours. Toss mixture occasionally.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: rice salad (low-fat)
directions: In medium saucepan, bring the water to boil.
Stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes; cool.
In a large bowl, mix the rice with remaining ingredients except the dressing.
Stir in 1/2 cup of dressing.
Toss to mix well.
Chill. Just before serving, toss with remaining dressing to taste.

title: ground ham on pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine ham, mustard, mayonnaise and brown sugar in a bowl.
Mix well. Grease cookie sheet and place pineapple slices on the cookie sheet.
Using an ice cream scoop or spoon, scoop ham mixture onto pineapple slices.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cucumbers and onions
directions: Slice the cucumbers and onions.
Put salt over them.
Let set for 1 hour. Wash good.
Mix the vinegar and sugar well.
Pour over the cucumbers and onions. Cover tightly and chill.

title: crock-pot lasagna
directions: brown ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet. Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt and oregano. Cook long enough to get it warm. Spoon a layer of meat sauce onto bottom of the slow cooker. Add a double layer of uncooked lasagna noodles, break to fit. And top with cheeses. Repeat with sauce, noodles and cheeses until all are used up. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients in continuance order from top to bottom, ending with zucchini.
Put mixture in 9 x 5-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 330° and bake 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fiesta mexican pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add half of process cheese spread and chili powder.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in tomato.
Combine remaining cheese, eggs, flour, salt and milk.
Beat until smooth. Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Spoon meat mixture over batter to 1 inch of edge.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces.
Sprinkle dressing over vegetables.
Add mayonnaise and sour cream.
Mix and chill.
Add tomatoes and onions for variety.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: my banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg.
Then add mashed bananas, flour, baking soda and spice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. May add 1/2 to 1 cup walnuts (optional).

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and drain, then put whole can of chicken with rice soup in.
Add can of cream of mushroom soup, enchilada sauce, green chilies, garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
This will be the sauce.
Layer ingredients:
first corn tortillas, sauce and Jack cheese (two layers).
Top with black olives.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef, onion salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Drain well; add kidney beans.
Mix in lettuce, cheese, tomatoes, avocado and cucumber.
Add Doritos and dressing.

title: settler beans
directions: Brown beef, onion and bacon together.
Drain.
Add both sugars, molasses, catsup, mustard and all the beans.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate pecan caramels
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with foil. Butter foil with 1 tablespoon butter. Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips. Set aside.

title: pina colada cake
directions: To cake mix add 4 eggs, milk, water and pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Punch holes in cake and pour cream of coconut over hot cake.
Let cool.
Spread Cool Whip over cake and sprinkle toasted coconut on top of Cool Whip.

title: herb and parsley dumplings
directions: Cut shortening into flour, spices, baking powder and salt with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in milk. Drop dough by spoonfuls onto hot meat or vegetables in boiling stew or thick soup.
Try not to drop directly into liquid.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
(I use these for homemade, from scratch chicken and dumplings.)

title: cupboard chicken casserole
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package directions, except using only 2 cups of water.
Cook just until water is absorbed. In a large mixing bowl, combine Rice-A-Roni, chicken (1 cup cooked, leftover chicken or turkey may be substituted), soup, cheese and broccoli.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish and bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake 15 to 20 minutes more.
This serves 4 generously and freezes well.

title: shepherd pie
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Sprinkle gravy mix on meat.
Add approximately 1/4 cup water and stir.
Spread meat mixture into 10-inch pan.
Spread potatoes on top.
Grate cheese over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in oven at 375° until brown.
Serve with vegetables and hot rolls.

title: marie-claude gracias chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using 1 tablespoon of butter, generously grease 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: christmas quiche
directions: Place prepared pie crust in a 9-inch pie pan.
Combine 1 1/2 cup grated Swiss cheese and 4 tablespoon flour.
Sprinkle into pie shell.
Sprinkle on 1/2 cup diced ham or salami.
Combine 3 eggs, 1 cup milk or light cream, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon mustard.
Beat until smooth and pour evenly over cheese.
Place unbaked pie in freezer until solid.
When ready to bake, place frozen pie in 400° oven for nearly 1 hour.
Cool slightly.
Garnish with chopped parsley and pimento.

title: potato salad
directions: Clean potato skins.
Cut potatoes into chunks and then boil. Boil eggs.
In the food processor, chop celery, peppers and onions.
Chop eggs.
Put ingredients in bowl.
Add relish, sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar and mustard.
Mix ingredients together. Add seasonings to your desired taste.
Chill salad.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle with pecans or parsley.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: ruth's crumb cake
directions: Add the eggs, oil and milk to the cake mix.
Mix all ingredients together; beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Bake in greased pan (about 16 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch) for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: complete breakfast casserole
directions: Night Before:
Fit slices of buttered bread snugly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top each slice with 2 slices boiled ham and 2 slices of cheese.
Top with slices of buttered bread (butter side down).

title: garden peas french-style
directions: In a casserole dish, combine well washed peas, onions and lettuce hearts cut into strips.
Then add butter, salt, pepper and sugar.
Pour enough water to cover peas.
Cover and simmer for about 1/2 hour.
Uncover and continue cooking over high heat if sauce is too liquidy.
Serves 6 persons.

title: cuban picadillo
directions: Mix meat well.
Saute all other ingredients; mix in meat, then mix tomato sauce in.
If needed, add some water to make more sauce. Cook until meat is done.
Have some fluffy white rice cooked separately.
Serve picadillo over the rice or to one side.
This and a salad make a meal.

title: oatmeal chocolate-chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand 5 minutes.

Stir into oats the margarine, brown sugar and granulated sugar. Let margarine melt, then add dry ingredients. Stir with spoon and add 1/3 cup chocolate chips. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
(Glass pan at 325°.)

title: hot and sour chinese soup
directions: Soak mushrooms in boiling water in a small bowl for 15 minutes. Drain, discard stems and slice caps.
Combine broth, soy sauce, mushrooms, bamboo shoots and pork in medium pan. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 3 minutes. Add bean curd, lemon juice and pepper. Bring to a boil.

title: cocktail drumsticks
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour over wings/drumsticks in large shallow pan.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: pizza dog
directions: Slash hot dog lengthwise, but not completely through.
Place in bun.
Spread center of hot dog with pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with seasoning and cheese.
Microwave on High for 35 to 40 seconds.

title: sweet holiday yams
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, orange juice, butter and salt.
Simmer over low heat until slightly thickened.
Place yams in greased casserole.
Pour sauce over and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook all together for 3 1/2 hours.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat one egg white stiff.
Add sugar, 2 eggs, salt and seasoning.
Add lukewarm milk.
Put in an unbaked crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake until custard is set.

title: lemon-cream sauce
directions: Combine
flour and sugar in top of double boiler.
With spoon, beat
in
cup
water,
egg, lemon peel and juice. Cook, stirring,
over boiling water until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter;
refrigerate until well chilled, at least 1 hour.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet, defrost and separate broccoli in oil. Blend onion and pepper; cook a short time.
Stir in soup, milk and 1/2 cup cheese.
Fold in rice and mix well.
Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Drain peppers.
Dry on paper towels and set aside.
Slice wafer meat thin in cubes.
Microwave on High for 1 minute or until crisp like bacon.
Let cool and break up.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in saucepan except carrots.
Pour sauce over carrots and keep warm until serving.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Grease pan.
Place peaches on bottom of 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs. Toss with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crab and shrimp salad
directions: The day before, mix together bread, eggs and onion; put in a large plastic bag and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add mayonnaise, crab meat, shrimp and celery, and mix well.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and shortening.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk and 3 1/2 cups flour and vanilla.
Mix well and add 1 cup flour and baking powder, sifted together.
Add last 1/2 cup buttermilk with soda dissolved.
Drop and bake at 375°.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix together.
Put in muffin tins and bake for 20 to 25 minutes in preheated 400° oven.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 425.
In medium bowl, stir together first 4 ingredients; cut in butter with a fork or pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
